Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.00,0:00:10.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,毛毛原创字幕，不太完善，转载请注明出处
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:15.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)\c&H00FFFF&}字幕转制｜{\b1\c&HFFFFFF&}天外生物\N{\b0\c&H079FFF&}感谢原字幕制作者
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.70,0:01:22.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,把他带这来\N{\rENG}Bring him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.57,0:01:25.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,在我们祖先那时候\N{\rENG}In the time of our ancestors
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.57,0:01:31.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们族人的循环再世位置就在孩子的手中\N{\rENG}the cycle of our people lay in the hands of the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.44,0:01:35.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,在部落中孩子是造物主留下的\N{\rENG}A child's position in the tribe was left to the maker.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.44,0:01:38.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,孩子的方位标志显现要早于大人\N{\rENG}Children bearing marks were brought before the elders
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.98,0:01:42.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,这儿，它们是被赐予的标记\N{\rENG}there, they were given titles...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.45,0:01:45.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,这些标记将跟随他一生\N{\rENG}...titles that would last a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.99,0:01:51.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,智慧\N{\rENG}Wisdom...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.73,0:01:55.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,勇气\N{\rENG}Courage...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.83,0:02:00.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,想象力\N{\rENG}Vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.77,0:02:08.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个孩子有着我们祖先\N{\rENG}This boy holds the holy marks
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.68,0:02:11.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,神圣的标记\N{\rENG}of our ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.75,0:02:15.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,他会是个领导者\N{\rENG}He is a leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.02,0:02:19.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,他会是个先知\N{\rENG}He is a prophet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.72,0:02:22.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们应该听从他\N{\rENG}We should listen to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.73,0:02:26.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们应该听从他\N{\rENG}We should listen to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.00,0:02:38.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,{{\fad(1500,1500)\i1\fs80\fsp30\pos(950,535)}一个国家的诞生
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.66,0:03:02.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我看见你了\N{\rENG}I see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.51,0:03:19.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,纳特\N{\rENG}Nat?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.98,0:03:23.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,纳特\N{\rENG}Nat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.82,0:03:26.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，你又赢了\N{\rENG}All right, you win again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.12,0:03:28.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,出来\N{\rENG}Come on out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.70,0:03:42.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,萨姆？过来吃晚饭了\N{\rENG}Sam? You come on in here for supper!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.54,0:03:44.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}Yessum.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.21,0:03:45.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,再见，纳特\N{\rENG}Bye, nat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.81,0:03:47.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,再见\N{\rENG}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.59,0:05:38.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,你就像蝙蝠的眼睛\N{\rENG}You so much as bat an eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.92,0:05:41.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要把你从这打回地狱去\N{\rENG}I'm gonna blow you from here to hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.66,0:05:43.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,你在外面做什么，伙计？\N{\rENG}What you doin' out here, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.73,0:05:46.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,从我的主人那装点食物\N{\rENG}Pickin' up some food for my master,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.19,0:05:47.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,本杰明 特纳\N{\rENG}Benjamin Turner.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.83,0:05:50.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,在午夜时间？转过来\N{\rENG}In the middle of the night? Turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.14,0:05:57.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,你的通行许可在哪？\N{\rENG}here your pass at?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.14,0:06:02.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,拿过来，快点\N{\rENG}Bring it on. C'mon! Bring it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.71,0:06:05.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,退回去\N{\rENG}Get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.85,0:06:09.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,你觉得你比我聪明，是不是？\N{\rENG}You think you're smarter than me, don't you, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.59,0:06:12.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有，先生\N{\rENG}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.15,0:06:13.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,杰西，我们怎么叫黑鬼的\N{\rENG}Jesse, who do we call a nigger
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.66,0:06:16.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,谁会觉得他比一个白人更精明？\N{\rENG}who done think he can outsmart a white man?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.16,0:06:17.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,死了的黑鬼\N{\rENG}A dead nigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.99,0:06:19.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,转过来\N{\rENG}Turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.73,0:06:24.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,跪下\N{\rENG}On your knees.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.67,0:06:31.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是你自己找的\N{\rENG}You done this to yourself, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.36,0:06:51.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 发生什么了？ － 上床去\N{\rENG}- What happened?  - Go on to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.63,0:06:53.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,我偷食物被抓了\N{\rENG}I got caught stealing food.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.36,0:06:58.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,我杀了看守，我得逃走了\N{\rENG}I killed a slave catcher. I gotta go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.03,0:07:00.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,你照顾好你母亲和娜娜，知道吗？\N{\rENG}You take care of your mom and Nana, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.80,0:07:02.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是神的孩子\N{\rENG}You a child of god.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.10,0:07:05.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,你意志坚定\N{\rENG}You got purpose. It's in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.04,0:07:06.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,上帝把它放在了这\N{\rENG}The lord put it there,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.91,0:07:09.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有任何人和事可以把它们夺走\N{\rENG}and there ain't nothing nobody can do to take it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.85,0:07:11.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,你明白了？\N{\rENG}You hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.08,0:07:12.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.38,0:07:15.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在你上床去\N{\rENG}Now you go ahead on and go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.92,0:07:18.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可能快点回来\N{\rENG}I'll be back for y'all as soon as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.73,0:07:31.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,回床上去，我们睡觉\N{\rENG}Go on back to bed. Go on to bed, girl! We sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.08,0:07:52.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,布里奇特，南希，起来了\N{\rENG}Bridget! Nancy! Y'all wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.42,0:07:53.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,艾萨克有大麻烦了\N{\rENG}Isaac's in a lot of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.96,0:07:57.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我需要你们当中的人告诉我他去哪里了\N{\rENG}I need one of y'all to tell me where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.43,0:08:00.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,不知道去哪了，主人，我们一晚没见他\N{\rENG}Don't know where he is, massa. We ain't seen him all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.30,0:08:01.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,你确定\N{\rENG}You sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.36,0:08:04.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,本，我命令你离开\N{\rENG}Ben, I'm gonna ask you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.43,0:08:08.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 嗯？ - 今晚一个白人丧命了\N{\rENG}- Huh?  - A white man has lost his life tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.14,0:08:10.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道这样说代表着接下去要发生什么样的事，走\N{\rENG}You know like I do what that mean. Get!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.84,0:08:12.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在，我要给他们些颜色看看\N{\rENG}Now, any harm done to these people,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.77,0:08:14.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要报告警长，我是认真的\N{\rENG}I'm gonna call the sheriff! I'm serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.98,0:08:22.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们没人知道他在那？\N{\rENG}None of y'all know where he is, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.45,0:08:24.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有，先生\N{\rENG}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.99,0:08:29.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,他妈的\N{\rENG}Goddamnit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.46,0:08:34.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道吗，孩子？\N{\rENG}What about you, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.73,0:08:35.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,他也什么不知道\N{\rENG}He don't know nothing, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.01,0:08:51.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,你父亲在那？\N{\rENG}Where's your daddy at?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.82,0:08:58.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,听着，你不告诉我他在那\N{\rENG}Now listen, you don't tell me where he's at,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.32,0:09:00.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,其它人也会找到他\N{\rENG}someone else is gonna find him,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.06,0:09:03.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们会杀了他\N{\rENG}and they gonna kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.19,0:09:07.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,你告诉我，我会安全把他带回来\N{\rENG}You tell me, I'll go get him.I'll bring him back here safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.76,0:09:08.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吗？\N{\rENG}All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.17,0:09:13.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,告诉我你父亲在哪\N{\rENG}Tell me where daddy's at.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.50,0:09:19.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,说话，不要一言不发\N{\rENG}Say it. Spit something outta that mouth! Say it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.84,0:09:22.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,告诉我在哪\N{\rENG}Tell me where he's at!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.05,0:09:27.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,他妈的\N{\rENG}Goddamnit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.18,0:09:32.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是那个黑鬼的孩子，好吧\N{\rENG}You that nigger's boy, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.22,0:09:35.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果让我发现你在说谎\N{\rENG}If I find out y'all's been lying,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.12,0:09:38.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,我会再回来的，到时我就不客气了\N{\rENG}I'm gonna come back here, i ain't gonna be so nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.79,0:09:41.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,主人，不要，不要，上帝啊！\N{\rENG}Oh, massa, please! Please! Massa, please! Oh, lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.80,0:09:43.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,够了，住手\N{\rENG}All right, that's... That's enough! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.37,0:09:47.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,你最好教教那个孩子礼貌\N{\rENG}You best teach that boy some manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.54,0:09:49.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,下次，他要用眼睛看着我\N{\rENG}Next time he look me in the eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.20,0:09:52.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,你父亲也会是这个结果\N{\rENG}you gonna get the same thing what waitin' for his pa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.89,0:10:14.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,可以帮你吗？\N{\rENG}Mind if I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.10,0:10:17.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,不用了\N{\rENG}No, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.10,0:10:18.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,萨缪尔告诉我早上的事情了\N{\rENG}Samuel told me something this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.97,0:10:20.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想要向你打听下\N{\rENG}I wanted to ask you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.90,0:10:26.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,他说纳特知道怎么读\N{\rENG}He said, nat knows how to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.91,0:10:28.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,纳特不知道怎么读\N{\rENG}Nat don't not know how to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.41,0:10:31.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,做为我自己是不相信的\N{\rENG}Part of me couldn't believe it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.11,0:10:34.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我测试了他\N{\rENG}So I tested him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.92,0:10:37.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,十分肯定\N{\rENG}Sure enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.92,0:10:40.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,他就在哪大声朗读\N{\rENG}there he was sounding out letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.42,0:10:45.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,你明天午饭后把他带来\N{\rENG}You have him come by the house tomorrow after lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.26,0:10:47.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,他没有恶意\N{\rENG}He don't mean no harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.13,0:10:49.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,下次我看见他我会抽他一顿\N{\rENG}I'ma whip him good the next time I see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.26,0:10:53.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,抽他？不要\N{\rENG}Whip him? Nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.93,0:10:56.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要教育他\N{\rENG}I'm gonna teach him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.94,0:11:00.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果万能的主给了这个孩子阅读的能力\N{\rENG}If the good lord gave that boy a gift to read,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.44,0:11:03.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们就不应该怠慢它，浪费它\N{\rENG}we'd be remiss to let it go to waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.28,0:11:06.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不要希望他能任何时候都能回家\N{\rENG}And don't expect him back anytime soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.95,0:11:09.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,他会和我们在主屋一起生活一段时间\N{\rENG}He'll be living with us in the main house for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.45,0:11:13.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,课程最好在开始时就不要被打断\N{\rENG}Lessons best not be disturbed in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.29,0:11:15.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，夫人\N{\rENG}Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.64,0:11:38.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,没关系，孩子，不是真的\N{\rENG}It's okay, baby. It's okay. It ain't real.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.18,0:11:42.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是真的，没事了，它在你的心里\N{\rENG}It ain't real. It's all right. It's in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.18,0:11:44.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,它在你的心里\N{\rENG}It's in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.25,0:11:46.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,妈妈在这\N{\rENG}Momma's here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.32,0:11:51.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要父亲\N{\rENG}Want my poppa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.33,0:11:55.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也是的，孩子\N{\rENG}Me too, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.66,0:11:58.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也是\N{\rENG}Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.07,0:12:03.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,把你的手臂穿过去\N{\rENG}Put your arms through.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.51,0:12:08.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,多帅气\N{\rENG}How handsome.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.69,0:12:25.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,他会没事的\N{\rENG}He'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.76,0:12:58.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,这些书是给白人看的\N{\rENG}These books are for white folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.63,0:13:03.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,这里有着你无法理解的全部事情\N{\rENG}They're full of things your kind wouldn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.20,0:13:06.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是我会让你读一本特别的书\N{\rENG}But I do have a special one just for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.30,0:13:08.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,你猜是什么？\N{\rENG}And guess what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.27,0:13:10.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,是有史以来最好的一本书\N{\rENG}It's the best book ever written.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.64,0:13:19.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是个特别的孩子\N{\rENG}You're a special boy, Nathaniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.65,0:13:25.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,努力学习听从我的指令，知道吗？\N{\rENG}Study hard and heed my instructions, hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.65,0:13:28.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,你的人生\N{\rENG}Your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.16,0:13:30.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,将会与众不同\N{\rENG}it'll never be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.79,0:13:32.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,我能预见到\N{\rENG}I'll see to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.39,0:13:33.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,是，太太\N{\rENG}Yes, missus.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.80,0:13:42.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,创世纪，开始\N{\rENG}"Genesis. In the beginning..."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.17,0:13:44.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,开始\N{\rENG}In the beginning...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.34,0:13:46.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,这儿，这个词是这儿\N{\rENG}Here, this word here, "the."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.67,0:13:50.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是狡猾，机警\N{\rENG}That's tricky. Now, these letters "t-h."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.08,0:13:51.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,无论何时你看见他们\N{\rENG}<i> Whenever you see them...</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.41,0:13:54.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,洁净你的双手，罪人们\N{\rENG}"...cleanse your hands, ye sinners...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.52,0:13:58.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,心怀二意的人们，净化你们的心灵\N{\rENG}"And purify your hearts, ye double-minded.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.52,0:14:02.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,被折磨，悲哀，哭泣\N{\rENG}"Be afflicted, and mourn, and weep.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.46,0:14:06.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,让你的笑声变成了悲哀\N{\rENG}"Let your laughter be turned to mourning,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.36,0:14:10.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,和你的快乐变成忧伤\N{\rENG}"and your joy to heaviness."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.07,0:14:14.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,雅各书，第四章，第八至九篇\N{\rENG}James 4, chapter 8 and 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.38,0:14:33.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,随我翻到雅各书第一章\N{\rENG}Turn with me, if you would, to James 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.19,0:14:38.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,握着耶和华的恩惠\N{\rENG}Holding on to the goodness of the lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.13,0:14:45.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,在他去陪伴上帝之前，我曾对本说\N{\rENG}I spoke to Ben, before he went on to be with the lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.10,0:14:53.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,他觉得你作为一个农场工人会对我们家庭更有用\N{\rENG}He felt you'd be more useful to our family as a field hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.58,0:15:02.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很抱歉，纳特\N{\rENG}I'm sorry, nat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.47,0:15:22.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在，你要从这开始\N{\rENG}Now, you gonna start here,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.27,0:15:24.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,你要去远一点的地方开始工作\N{\rENG}and you're gonna work your way down yonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.61,0:15:26.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我会在这里，明白吗？\N{\rENG}And I'll be right over here. You hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.36,0:15:42.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.34,0:16:34.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢你，兄弟\N{\rENG}Thank you, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.92,0:16:46.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,我已经不省人事了，除非我有看见\N{\rENG}I had fainted, unless I had believed to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.85,0:16:49.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,上帝的善良\N{\rENG}the goodness of the lord
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.36,0:16:52.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,在我们生活的土地上\N{\rENG}in the land of the living.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.69,0:16:56.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,等待上帝的到来\N{\rENG}Wait on the lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.86,0:16:58.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,要变的善良勇敢\N{\rENG}be of good courage,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.67,0:17:01.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,他会使你的内心强大\N{\rENG}and he shall strengthen thine heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.44,0:17:06.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,等会，我说\N{\rENG}Wait, I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.54,0:17:08.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,依靠上帝\N{\rENG}on the lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.75,0:17:13.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我们低下我们的头颅\N{\rENG}Let us bow our heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.89,0:17:22.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,萨姆，那是你姐姐？\N{\rENG}Sam, that sister of yours,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:24.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,真是能成为个好老婆\N{\rENG}gonna make a fine wife indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.39,0:17:27.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,我说的是真的\N{\rENG}It's been a true blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.73,0:17:31.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,看着她变成一个女人\N{\rENG}seeing her develop into the woman that she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.90,0:17:33.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,这可是个美好的祝福\N{\rENG}It'd be an even better blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.40,0:17:34.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,看她和她的母亲\N{\rENG}seein' her and momma
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.61,0:17:37.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,她们把脚放在他桌子下而不是我的\N{\rENG}put their feet under his table instead of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.65,0:17:51.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,我得说\N{\rENG}I gotta say,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.75,0:17:55.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,萨姆，你的奴隶确信知道怎么守规矩\N{\rENG}Sam, your slaves sure do know how to behave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.42,0:17:58.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,每次我来都令我印象深刻\N{\rENG}I'm impressed with them every time I come around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.29,0:18:00.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，他们当中有个牧师\N{\rENG}Well, they god fearin'. One of them's a preacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.60,0:18:01.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,没人告诉我\N{\rENG}No one's gotta tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.76,0:18:04.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,干旱的日子真是太难熬了\N{\rENG}the times are tough with the drought.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.43,0:18:07.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这个国家对白人来说变得更艰难了\N{\rENG}It's gettin' harder for the whites in this county
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.80,0:18:10.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,要给他们的黑人奴隶吃好穿好\N{\rENG}to clothe and feed their niggers good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.61,0:18:12.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,这些关于暴动的谈论\N{\rENG}Talks of insurrection
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.61,0:18:14.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,让白人家伙感到害怕\N{\rENG}got folks scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.08,0:18:18.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,我觉得人们应该付出更好的工资报酬\N{\rENG}I think people might pay good money
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.68,0:18:21.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,可以让这些人能更冷静些\N{\rENG}to have them calm down a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.08,0:18:23.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,特别是一个他们自己人\N{\rENG}Especially by one of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.09,0:18:35.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,噢\N{\rENG}Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.46,0:18:40.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看见一个黑鬼从这跑过吗？\N{\rENG}You seen a nigger run past here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.47,0:18:43.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,我睡着了没看见\N{\rENG}Naw. Then again i doze off for a few.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:44.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看见了吗，孩子？\N{\rENG}What about you, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.74,0:18:48.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,最好现在不要撒谎，你骗不过我的\N{\rENG}Best not lie now. I know when y'all's lyin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.81,0:18:51.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有，先生\N{\rENG}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.11,0:18:52.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,两个比尔琼斯地方的\N{\rENG}Couple of niggers went missin'
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.61,0:18:53.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,黑鬼不见了今天早上\N{\rENG}off bill Johnson's place this mornin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.98,0:18:55.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,说是在逃跑之前\N{\rENG}Say they raised up on an overseer
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.62,0:18:57.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们举起了工头\N{\rENG}before they took off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.09,0:19:00.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，看见什么就告诉我\N{\rENG}All right, you see somethin' let us know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.89,0:19:02.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}Will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.42,0:19:03.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,驾\N{\rENG}Giddyup.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.83,0:19:14.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你把这里结束了，我去广场里面\N{\rENG}You finish up here, I'll go square up inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.00,0:19:15.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，先生\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.85,0:19:30.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,夫人，杨斯掉了这个\N{\rENG}Ma'am. The youngin', he dropped this a step back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.85,0:19:32.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rENG}Thank ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.02,0:19:38.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,你在干什么那？\N{\rENG}Whatcha think you're doin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.99,0:19:42.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,他只是…你和我妻子说话了\N{\rENG}He was just tryin'... You spoke to my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.83,0:19:44.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,你主人在那？\N{\rENG}Where's your owner, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.67,0:19:48.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,问你话那\N{\rENG}I asked you a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.74,0:19:55.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,你最好收起你的棍子来\N{\rENG}You best goin' to put that stick down now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.88,0:19:57.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要找警长了\N{\rENG}I want the sheriff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.01,0:19:58.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个家伙羞辱了我\N{\rENG}his boy assaulted me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.95,0:20:00.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,他羞辱了我妻子\N{\rENG}He assaulted my wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.58,0:20:01.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要指控他\N{\rENG}And I'm bringin' charges!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.75,0:20:02.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,弗洛伊德警长？\N{\rENG}Sheriff Floyd?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.85,0:20:04.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，他归你了，如果你喜欢\N{\rENG}All right, you fetch him if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.79,0:20:06.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,但同时我数三下\N{\rENG}But in the meantime i will give you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.05,0:20:08.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,你把棍子放下来\N{\rENG}to the count of three to put your stick down
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.06,0:20:09.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,在我给你一些真实的指控之前\N{\rENG}before I give you some real charges
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.42,0:20:10.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,让他回到这里\N{\rENG}to give him when he gets here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.66,0:20:11.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,你威胁我\N{\rENG}You threatnin' me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.93,0:20:13.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,一\N{\rENG}One.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.06,0:20:15.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,二\N{\rENG}Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.90,0:20:19.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,走吧，带着孩子\N{\rENG}C'mon, get the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.57,0:20:21.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,回家\N{\rENG}Let's get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.69,0:20:41.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们的玉米很甜\N{\rENG}We got sweet corn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.09,0:20:42.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,来吧，来点玉米粉\N{\rENG}C'mon now! Get your grits!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.56,0:20:43.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们这玉米很甜\N{\rENG}We got sweet corn here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.93,0:20:46.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,看一看\N{\rENG}Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.13,0:20:47.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这的这个\N{\rENG}And this one here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.96,0:20:49.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,强壮如牛\N{\rENG}Strong as an ox!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.76,0:20:52.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,虽然不起眼，但是年轻的体内流动着活力的种子\N{\rENG}Nothin' but good seed flowin' from this here buck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.03,0:20:53.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,看看他们的牙齿\N{\rENG}Look at them teeth. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.80,0:20:55.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,我将开始拍卖\N{\rENG}I'll start him out at...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.77,0:20:57.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,两百\N{\rENG}200.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.24,0:20:59.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,一百五\N{\rENG}150?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.77,0:21:02.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,拜托了，我还得在这接着混那\N{\rENG}C'mon now, I gotta make a living here, gents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.11,0:21:05.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,一百？七十五？\N{\rENG}100? 75?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.25,0:21:07.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,成交，带走吧\N{\rENG}Sold! Get outta here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.62,0:21:10.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,给他套上束具，带那个女过来\N{\rENG}Put a yoke on him. Bring her up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.65,0:21:16.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在，大家可以考虑下这个标致的乡下妞\N{\rENG}Now, consider this comely wench.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.49,0:21:20.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,不超过十八岁\N{\rENG}Not a day over 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.63,0:21:23.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，我从一百七十五元开始起拍\N{\rENG}All right, I'll start her off at 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.63,0:21:26.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,我出一百七十五元，还有出价的吗？\N{\rENG}I got 175. Do I hear two?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.90,0:21:30.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在出价两百二十五了\N{\rENG}Now we're talkin'! Do I got 225?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.64,0:21:32.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,主人，那个乡下女孩可以当作礼物送给\N{\rENG}Massa, that wench there sure would make
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.01,0:21:33.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,凯瑟琳小姐\N{\rENG}a good weddin' gift for miss Catherine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.64,0:21:34.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,两百二十五\N{\rENG}225!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.74,0:21:36.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,你一直在说小姐在问你\N{\rENG}You keep sayin' she been askin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.04,0:21:37.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,你出两百五吗？\N{\rENG}Do I hear 250?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.21,0:21:39.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,她看着十分年轻，如果你问我的话\N{\rENG}She looks right young, if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.01,0:21:40.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,快点！\N{\rENG}C'mon now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.01,0:21:41.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,对的，先生，她很年轻，给我两百五\N{\rENG}You right, sir, she young. Gimme 250.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.85,0:21:44.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是如果跟对人的话\N{\rENG}C'mon. But with the right teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.29,0:21:46.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 一个像这样的姑娘？ - 两百五\N{\rENG}- a wench like that?  - 250.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.82,0:21:47.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,可以工作很长一段时间了\N{\rENG}Could be workin' a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.99,0:21:50.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,两百七十五元\N{\rENG}There it is! 275?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.69,0:21:52.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,主人，我们应该\N{\rENG}Massa, sure would be a shame to watch her
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.26,0:21:54.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,用一个低价买了她\N{\rENG}go to waste for such a low price.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.83,0:21:56.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道个屁\N{\rENG}And what the hell would you know about
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.03,0:21:58.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么是高什么是低？\N{\rENG}what's a little and what's a lot, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.83,0:22:00.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道你最近怎么了\N{\rENG}I don't know what's gotten into you lately,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.90,0:22:02.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,但不论是什么，你最好放弃\N{\rENG}but whatever it is, you better quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.57,0:22:04.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看见我看到的了吗？\N{\rENG}Are you seein' what I'm seein'?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.84,0:22:08.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,你带着个回家\N{\rENG}You take this one home, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.68,0:22:10.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,把她洗干净了\N{\rENG}clean her up,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.08,0:22:12.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要太久\N{\rENG}won't be long before you find yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.71,0:22:14.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,你会比玩球的小狗还要高兴的\N{\rENG}happier than a dog with three balls!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.02,0:22:17.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,笑一笑，贱货\N{\rENG}Smile, bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.69,0:22:20.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,两百五一次\N{\rENG}That's 250 goin' once.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.29,0:22:24.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,两百五两次\N{\rENG}250 goin' twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.83,0:22:27.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 两百七十五  - 两百七十五\N{\rENG}- 275  - 275.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.06,0:22:29.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们出两百七十五\N{\rENG}We got 275!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.83,0:22:32.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,两百七十五一次\N{\rENG}275 goin' once.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.30,0:22:36.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,两百七十五两次\N{\rENG}275 goin' twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.84,0:22:40.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,卖给后排那个善良的绅士了\N{\rENG}Sold to that fine gentleman in the back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.05,0:22:47.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,喔\N{\rENG}Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.88,0:22:52.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,她没事的，先生\N{\rENG}She be fine, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.22,0:22:54.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,我希望你是对的\N{\rENG}I sure hope you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.72,0:22:57.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,你妈给她洗过吃了\N{\rENG}Have your momma get her cleaned and fed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.22,0:22:59.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 先从擦地板开始  - 明白，先生\N{\rENG}- Start breakin' her in.  - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.60,0:23:01.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,你和汉克可以从北面围栏那开始\N{\rENG}You and hark can start on the north fence
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.10,0:23:03.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这是明早的第一件事  - 明白，先生\N{\rENG}- first thing in the morning.  - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.37,0:23:11.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不会伤害你的\N{\rENG}I ain't gonna hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.01,0:23:13.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,只是爬上来帮你出来\N{\rENG}Just gonna climb up and help you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.08,0:23:20.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,没事的\N{\rENG}It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.74,0:23:46.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,这孩子是谁？发生了什么？\N{\rENG}Who is this child? What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.31,0:23:48.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,活力四射\N{\rENG}Burnin' up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.11,0:23:51.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,是我的，这是我的裙子\N{\rENG}This mine! This my dress! My dress! This my dress!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.85,0:23:53.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,走开，出去\N{\rENG}Go now! Get out, ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.05,0:23:57.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们不会伤害你\N{\rENG}We're not gonna hurt you. We're not gonna hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.22,0:23:58.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要带走\N{\rENG}Don't take it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.79,0:24:33.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,笑一下\N{\rENG}You just smile
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.95,0:24:35.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,让他们可以谈话，好吗？\N{\rENG}and let them do the talkin'. All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.82,0:24:37.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}Yessum.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.96,0:24:48.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,中午好，主人，这是切瑞安妮\N{\rENG}Afternoon, massa. This here cherry-Ann.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.44,0:24:49.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,主人\N{\rENG}Massa.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.47,0:24:52.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,凯瑟琳娜\N{\rENG}Catherine!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.04,0:24:56.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,凯瑟琳娜，这是切瑞安妮\N{\rENG}Catherine, this here is cherry-Ann.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.81,0:24:57.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,夫人\N{\rENG}Missus.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.15,0:25:02.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\rENG}Oh, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.28,0:25:07.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,来吧，见下我母亲\N{\rENG}Come on, i want you to meet momma.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.16,0:25:13.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,母亲\N{\rENG}Momma.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.16,0:25:15.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.46,0:25:17.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,为了什么\N{\rENG}For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.83,0:25:22.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,你让她边得更好更漂亮了\N{\rENG}For gettin' her better. For makin' her so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.04,0:25:24.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,我什么也没做\N{\rENG}I didn't do nothin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.34,0:25:26.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,那些美貌\N{\rENG}That girl was brought into this world
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.21,0:25:28.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,都是那女孩与生俱来的\N{\rENG}as beautiful as she could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.02,0:25:41.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,很难过看到你和太太要走了\N{\rENG}It sure is sad to see you and the missus go.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.19,0:25:42.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们只是隔了一条路\N{\rENG}We'll be just down the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.89,0:25:44.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,当我们都安顿好了\N{\rENG}When we get all good and settled,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.09,0:25:45.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们会回来看看的\N{\rENG}we'll come back and visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.36,0:25:47.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,周日去教堂之后\N{\rENG}On Sundays for church and that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.50,0:25:49.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，不急的\N{\rENG}Well, there's no rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.23,0:25:51.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,我开玩笑的，来这\N{\rENG}Oh. I'm foolin'. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.87,0:25:53.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你有需要\N{\rENG}If y'all need anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.10,0:25:56.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,或者他对你不好，让我知道\N{\rENG}or he ain't treatin' you right, you let me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.37,0:25:58.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，哥哥，我爱你\N{\rENG}Yes, big brother. I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.31,0:26:00.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也爱你\N{\rENG}Love you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.17,0:26:01.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,母亲，你准备好了吗？\N{\rENG}Momma, you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.78,0:26:09.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很担心你，萨姆\N{\rENG}I'm worried about you, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.02,0:26:11.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,你要独自面对这么大的一个地方\N{\rENG}This a big place to be out here all by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.89,0:26:13.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,我没事的\N{\rENG}I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.89,0:26:20.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,你要小心\N{\rENG}You take care now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.90,0:26:22.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}All right. Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.90,0:26:32.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,主人，为马准备的\N{\rENG}Massa. For the horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.07,0:26:34.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,就一个\N{\rENG}Just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.48,0:26:35.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，先生\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.08,0:26:43.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨\N{\rENG}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.42,0:26:45.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨\N{\rENG}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.56,0:26:50.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是纳特\N{\rENG}I'm nat.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.19,0:26:51.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rENG}I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.09,0:26:55.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,不好意思\N{\rENG}Sorry for
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.10,0:26:58.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,打扰你了\N{\rENG}fightin' you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.07,0:27:00.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,没事\N{\rENG}Oh, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.97,0:27:04.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯…\N{\rENG}Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.45,0:27:15.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,它们很漂亮\N{\rENG}They're pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.28,0:27:18.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这四周发现的\N{\rENG}Found them 'round here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.39,0:27:20.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.06,0:27:32.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,再见\N{\rENG}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.30,0:28:37.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像我们在\N{\rENG}Just as the planted crop
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.20,0:28:39.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,收割庄稼一样\N{\rENG}is harvested in its own time,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.07,0:28:42.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,主也在播种着我们\N{\rENG}so too has the lord planted us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.21,0:28:51.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,赞美主啊\N{\rENG}Good lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.55,0:28:56.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,赞美主啊\N{\rENG}The good lord, the good lord
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.22,0:28:59.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,当我们完成了主赐予我们的工作时\N{\rENG}will finish his work in us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.69,0:29:09.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,最后，我会敦促你们用心来敬奉上帝\N{\rENG}So, in closing, i urge you all to take heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.40,0:29:11.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,要用尽你们的一生\N{\rENG}for god is at work in your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.27,0:29:14.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,直到它的工作完成才算结束，阿门？\N{\rENG}and he will not stop until his job is done. Amen?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.13,0:29:15.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,阿门，解散\N{\rENG}Amen. Dismissed!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.08,0:29:23.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,仿佛命运已经注定永远\N{\rENG}It seems like it's been forever
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.48,0:29:26.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,自从我上次看见你起\N{\rENG}since I last seen you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.41,0:29:29.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们之间虽只有短短的几步\N{\rENG}There were a few miles between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.58,0:29:32.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,但我却感觉到很遥远\N{\rENG}Just feels like so many more.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.72,0:29:36.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,在哪过的还好吗？\N{\rENG}How is it there?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.26,0:29:41.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,很好，不像我以前待的地方\N{\rENG}It's fine. Not like what I come from 'fore here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.20,0:29:44.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,多数时间我都是在照顾伊丽莎白小姐\N{\rENG}Most days I'm just tending to miss Elizabeth
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.40,0:29:47.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,要不就是给凯瑟琳娜小姐拿这拿那的\N{\rENG}or fetching this-that for miss Catherine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.44,0:29:53.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你下周从教堂还回来的话？\N{\rENG}You know if y'all coming back next week for church?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.61,0:29:55.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很了解你\N{\rENG}I know as much as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.54,0:29:57.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,我猜想如果太太一直暗示下去\N{\rENG}I suppose if missus is suggesting it,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.75,0:30:00.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,里斯大人也不在意什么的\N{\rENG}master Reese don't mind the trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.45,0:30:05.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可不想等的太久才能见到你\N{\rENG}I sure wouldn't wanna wait another season to see ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.29,0:30:08.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也是的\N{\rENG}Me, neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.63,0:30:25.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是我奶奶从我爷爷那拿来的\N{\rENG}My Nana got it from my grandaddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.14,0:30:29.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,她被从非洲抓来时就一直带着它\N{\rENG}She brought it with her when she was taken from Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.48,0:30:32.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是唯一能让她的心灵感到自由的东西\N{\rENG}Said it was the only thing that kept her mind free.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.78,0:30:36.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,很漂亮\N{\rENG}It's pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.79,0:30:42.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,我把它送给你了\N{\rENG}I want you to have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.66,0:30:50.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,防止我有段时间不能见到你\N{\rENG}In case I don't see you for a while, you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.50,0:30:53.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个可以体醒你要时刻记住我\N{\rENG}have something that reminds you of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.17,0:31:00.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道是不是该收下\N{\rENG}I don't know if it's right I take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.84,0:31:03.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可没有能让你\N{\rENG}'Sides, I don't have nothing to give you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.61,0:31:05.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,思念我的东西给你\N{\rENG}to remind you of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.68,0:31:11.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,我已经对你念念不忘了\N{\rENG}I spend all my time thinkin' about you already.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.79,0:31:15.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,切瑞？\N{\rENG}Cherry?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.12,0:31:16.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,来帮下妈妈，可以走了\N{\rENG}Come help with momma. It's time to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.66,0:32:32.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,谁在那？\N{\rENG}Who there?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.51,0:32:42.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,纳特？\N{\rENG}Nat?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.91,0:32:48.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,你要干嘛？\N{\rENG}What are you doin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.26,0:33:00.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我应该早点这样做\N{\rENG}I shoulda done that earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.70,0:33:04.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,你就是专程来亲我的？\N{\rENG}You came here to kiss me?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.24,0:33:13.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\rENG}No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.38,0:33:19.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要的比这多\N{\rENG}I ain't got much.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.25,0:33:23.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的信仰，妈妈，奶奶\N{\rENG}My faith, momma, Nana.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.38,0:33:26.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,直到现在，我要的更多\N{\rENG}Up until now, enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.39,0:33:31.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,切瑞，我希望你可以成我的妻子，我会无比的荣幸\N{\rENG}Cherry, I'd feel right honored if you'd be my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.73,0:33:36.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我会对你好的，用我的一生来保护你\N{\rENG}I'd treat ya right. Protect ya with my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.56,0:33:38.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你嫁给我\N{\rENG}If you'd have me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.57,0:33:43.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,我愿意\N{\rENG}Yes. Yes, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.42,0:34:00.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,接下去怎么做？\N{\rENG}What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.49,0:34:01.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.76,0:34:04.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,我会和萨缪尔先生谈谈\N{\rENG}I talk it over with Samuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.26,0:34:06.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,给我们找个小屋子，等你下次来的时候就会布置一新了\N{\rENG}Get us a cabin set up when y'all visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.66,0:34:09.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.45,0:34:31.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,天父，我们今天齐聚一堂\N{\rENG}<i> Heavenly father.</i> <i> We are gathered here today</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.02,0:34:32.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,来参加这两个孩子的婚礼\N{\rENG}to join together these two children,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.92,0:34:36.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们找到了爱的真谛\N{\rENG}who have found the love that exists in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.66,0:34:40.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们一直沐浴在爱的怀抱中\N{\rENG}The love that surrounds all of us all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.29,0:34:43.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们祝福他们\N{\rENG}We bless these children together with our hands
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.80,0:34:47.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们手捧鲜花与爱\N{\rENG}that the love that flows through our hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.96,0:35:14.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,哈喽，教士\N{\rENG}Well, hello, reverend.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.96,0:35:16.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,我没指望能在\N{\rENG}I wasn't expecting to see you around
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.70,0:35:17.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,周日见到你\N{\rENG}these parts 'till Sunday.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.96,0:35:19.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么风把你吹来的？\N{\rENG}What brings you around the middle of the week?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.83,0:35:21.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,永远不要在错误的时间\N{\rENG}Never a wrong time...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.84,0:35:24.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,给一个基督兄弟带来祝福\N{\rENG}...to bring a blessing to a brother in Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.40,0:35:25.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,噢，上帝\N{\rENG}Oh lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.61,0:35:27.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,这祝福要花钱吗？\N{\rENG}Is this blessing gonna cost me money?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.51,0:35:31.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个子也不要，实际从另一面来说\N{\rENG}Not a penny. To the contrary, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.51,0:35:33.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,艾塞亚，送点水来\N{\rENG}Isaiah, run us out a water.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.78,0:35:36.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,最好给我来些杜松子酒\N{\rENG}Gin, if you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.62,0:35:39.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要谈下关于你牧师的情况\N{\rENG}So, I put the word out about your preacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.99,0:35:45.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,有几个农民愿意出好价钱\N{\rENG}Got a couple of farmers willing to turn a good coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.96,0:35:47.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是吗？ - 嗯\N{\rENG}- Is that right?   - Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.83,0:35:51.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,这些天价格看涨\N{\rENG}Every bit counts these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.46,0:35:52.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦\N{\rENG}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.11,0:36:00.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,啊\N{\rENG}Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.57,0:36:03.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯…\N{\rENG}Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.61,0:36:05.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果他能满足他们的愿望\N{\rENG}If your boy does to their liking,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.75,0:36:07.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,你能大赚一笔\N{\rENG}you could get outta debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.38,0:36:09.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,拯救你的农场\N{\rENG}Save your farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.55,0:36:14.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有这些都只要纳特牧师出面就行了\N{\rENG}And all I gotta do is let nat preach.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.12,0:36:16.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,就这么简单\N{\rENG}That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.39,0:36:20.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不能担保这些家伙\N{\rENG}Now, I'm not vouching for the character of these fellas.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.39,0:36:23.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,是怎么运营这些生意的\N{\rENG}What business they runnin' or how.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.56,0:36:24.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就是来告诉你\N{\rENG}I'm just here to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.63,0:36:26.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,有个机会可以尝试下\N{\rENG}that there's an opportunity there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.47,0:36:29.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,你要做的就是好好利用它\N{\rENG}One you got the means to capitalize on.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.40,0:36:31.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们说的是哪里？\N{\rENG}Whereabouts we talkin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.17,0:36:33.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,是先从南安普敦开始的\N{\rENG}In southampton, at the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.04,0:36:35.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，听起来不错\N{\rENG}Well, sounds good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.64,0:36:37.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,细节我会在告诉你的\N{\rENG}I'll send you the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.04,0:36:41.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,姓名，地点，细节，我明天告诉你\N{\rENG}Names, locations, and dates, I'd say by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.52,0:36:43.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,你已经预定好时间了\N{\rENG}You already booked the dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.15,0:36:44.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就是来让你同意的\N{\rENG}I figured you'd say yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.75,0:36:47.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,你能得到什么好处？\N{\rENG}What's in it for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.75,0:36:52.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么好处也没有，就是为了帮助兄弟\N{\rENG}The pure joy of knowing that I'm helping a brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.06,0:36:54.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有，关键的来了\N{\rENG}And, uh... Oh, here it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.46,0:36:58.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，如果我能得到好处\N{\rENG}Well, if I was to receive a gift offering,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.06,0:37:01.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我当然也不会反对的\N{\rENG}I certainly wouldn't object.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.44,0:37:03.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你太小心了，教士\N{\rENG}You are caution, reverend.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.44,0:37:06.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是个侍奉上帝的仆人\N{\rENG}I am but a servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.45,0:37:17.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,好多咸肉和西红柿\N{\rENG}Here's some salt pork and some tomatoes
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.48,0:37:18.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,你饿的时候可以吃\N{\rENG}for when you get hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.79,0:37:20.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢你，母亲\N{\rENG}Thank you, momma.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.46,0:37:24.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要担心\N{\rENG}Don't y'all go getting' worried now.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.62,0:37:26.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我会安全返回的\N{\rENG}I'll be back directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.16,0:37:27.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rENG}I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.96,0:37:31.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,向上帝祈祷，你能平安返回\N{\rENG}Pray the lord brings you back safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.54,0:38:13.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是特纳家的黑鬼？\N{\rENG}You massa Turner's nigger?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.14,0:38:14.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是纳特\N{\rENG}I'm nat.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.77,0:38:17.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,特纳在里面\N{\rENG}Massa Turner's in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.52,0:38:24.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,来吧\N{\rENG}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.86,0:38:33.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我们到了？ - 是，先生\N{\rENG}- We're here?  - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.03,0:38:40.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,萨姆 特纳\N{\rENG}Sam Turner.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.10,0:38:43.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,真准时，约瑟芬 兰道尔\N{\rENG}Made it right on time. Joseph Randall.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.97,0:38:46.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是艾伯纳\N{\rENG}This here's abner.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.31,0:38:48.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,这小个子是杰斯帕\N{\rENG}This little one? Jasper.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.71,0:38:50.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是牧师？是的，先生\N{\rENG}This the preacher? Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.88,0:38:52.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,纳特？\N{\rENG}Nat?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.55,0:38:54.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,晚上好，先生\N{\rENG}Evening, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.55,0:38:56.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,他看着还是个小年轻？\N{\rENG}He's a little young, ain't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.05,0:38:57.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有，他蛮大了\N{\rENG}Why, he's old enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.72,0:38:59.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,他已经学习圣经很长一段时间了，是不是？\N{\rENG}You've been studying the word awhile, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.30,0:39:02.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,学习？\N{\rENG}Studyin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.70,0:39:06.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,我能勉强训练我的黑奴们学习他们自己的名字\N{\rENG}I can barely train my niggers to learn their own names.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.19,0:39:08.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,来吧\N{\rENG}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.20,0:39:16.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是艰难时刻\N{\rENG}<i> It's hard times</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.31,0:39:18.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,对于我和你这些小农场主来说\N{\rENG}<i> for small farmers</i> <i> like you and myself.</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.71,0:39:19.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在情况更糟糕了\N{\rENG}Breakin' even's hard enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.84,0:39:21.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,黑奴要想出入头地是不可能的\N{\rENG}but getting ahead's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.74,0:39:23.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只能做个好人\N{\rENG}So to save some,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.01,0:39:25.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,把他们带回来每天管顿饭吃\N{\rENG}I cut them back to a meal a day per head now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.31,0:39:27.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们当中有一小部分人开始变得不安躁动\N{\rENG}A few of them started getting' fidgety,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.35,0:39:29.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我让艾伯纳陪着我一起\N{\rENG}so I had abner come down on 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.02,0:39:32.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,艾伯纳，这儿，他是我唯一真正的护身符\N{\rENG}Abner, here, he's my only real protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.99,0:39:35.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在，这些黑奴让我不满意，你要和他们说\N{\rENG}Now, they needs to mind me. You speak on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.89,0:39:38.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们所有的财富都在天堂里\N{\rENG}They treasure in heaven from submittin' and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.93,0:39:42.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果他们感到悲伤或是继续这样\N{\rENG}If they gets to moanin' or carryin' on,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.13,0:39:43.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可以毫不怜悯的分文不给\N{\rENG}ou don't pay 'em no mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.76,0:39:45.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为他们太懒惰了就好像生活在地狱里\N{\rENG}because they lazy as all hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.23,0:39:47.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们出工不出力\N{\rENG}They do anything to get outta work.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.93,0:39:49.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,你准备好了吗，伙计？\N{\rENG}You ready, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.65,0:40:06.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,听着，今晚我请了牧师来\N{\rENG}Listen up! Got a preacher here tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.95,0:40:09.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,过来，孩子\N{\rENG}Come here, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.96,0:40:13.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们看他和你们一样都是黑人\N{\rENG}Now, he's a nigger here like y'all,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.29,0:40:15.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,他会告诉你们关于上帝的好处\N{\rENG}and he's here to talk to you about the lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.96,0:40:17.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们注意听着\N{\rENG}So you listen to him
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.70,0:40:22.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们照样做也可以上天堂的，知道吗？\N{\rENG}and you might just make it into heaven, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.17,0:40:56.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,兄弟姐妹\N{\rENG}Brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.67,0:41:06.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,我带你见彼得\N{\rENG}I lead you to Peter 2:18.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.21,0:41:12.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,奴隶们，奉献自己\N{\rENG}"Slaves, submit yourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.85,0:41:17.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,带着你所有的尊敬去你的主人那\N{\rENG}"to your masters with all respect."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.19,0:41:21.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,不仅那些好的和体贴\N{\rENG}"Not only to those who are good and considerate,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.86,0:41:27.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,但那些严厉的\N{\rENG}"but also to those who are harsh."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.77,0:41:38.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,你确定晚上不住这？\N{\rENG}You sure you don't wanna stay the night?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.04,0:41:39.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,拿些好的白兰地来\N{\rENG}Got some fine Brandy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.71,0:41:42.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,有几个女孩关在地窖里\N{\rENG}and a couple of choice wenches in the cellar.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.38,0:41:45.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,让艾伯纳来给我们拉小提琴\N{\rENG}Get abner here to strike out the fiddle
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.72,0:41:49.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,让女士和我们围坐在壁炉边\N{\rENG}and sit around the fire, tell some old lies, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.22,0:41:51.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,不了，我们要赶在太阳落山前回家\N{\rENG}No. We best be gettin' back before sun go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.73,0:41:54.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，你自便吧\N{\rENG}All right. Suit yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.89,0:41:56.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可以带瓶白兰地\N{\rENG}Would take a bottle of that Brandy,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.33,0:41:57.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你愿意分给我的话\N{\rENG}if you could spare it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.73,0:42:00.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,哦，小事一件，艾伯纳？\N{\rENG}Oh, sure thing. Abner?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.90,0:42:02.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,有了那个巧克力帮我办事\N{\rENG}I got a chocolate one here
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.77,0:42:06.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我可真是省力不少啊\N{\rENG}that does it right every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.24,0:42:08.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,你确定不要留下过夜了？\N{\rENG}You sure you don't wanna stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.91,0:42:11.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,不了，他们等着我们回去\N{\rENG}No, they expectin' us back. You know how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.78,0:42:13.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.35,0:42:18.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是个聪明人，萨姆\N{\rENG}You's a smart man, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.25,0:42:20.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,你带着那家伙前途光明\N{\rENG}Man make a fortune with that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.39,0:42:29.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,和你做生意很愉快\N{\rENG}Great doin' business with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.50,0:42:35.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,走吧\N{\rENG}Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.29,0:42:58.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,你还好吗？\N{\rENG}You all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.42,0:43:02.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,S\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.80,0:43:10.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,那边的那件衣服\N{\rENG}The dress there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.44,0:43:13.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,是你婚礼时穿过的吧？\N{\rENG}That the one you were wearing that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.81,0:43:17.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,对的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.14,0:43:19.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,是妈妈从她衣服里选给你的吗？\N{\rENG}Momma offered you one of hers?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.05,0:43:21.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}She did.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.00,0:43:42.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,阿比盖尔 海恩\N{\rENG}"Abigail hayne."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.00,0:43:44.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的母亲\N{\rENG}My momma.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.84,0:43:50.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,麦迪森海恩，那是谁？\N{\rENG}"Madison hayne." Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.18,0:43:53.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,是我\N{\rENG}That's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.01,0:43:56.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,我母亲\N{\rENG}My momma,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.02,0:44:00.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,她给我穿上这件裙子的时候\N{\rENG}she put this dress on me
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.19,0:44:03.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们把我从她身边夺走了\N{\rENG}the day they took me from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.49,0:44:07.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,看见这块补丁\N{\rENG}Showed me this here patch.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.19,0:44:11.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,它提醒着我永远不要忘了我是谁\N{\rENG}Told me to never forget who I was,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.20,0:44:14.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有我的母亲\N{\rENG}and that I had a momma.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.03,0:44:17.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,她就在某个地方\N{\rENG}And that she was somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.37,0:44:21.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我时刻都在思念着她，爱着她\N{\rENG}missing me and loving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.51,0:44:25.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,我那时十三岁\N{\rENG}I was 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.38,0:44:35.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果愿意我可以叫你麦迪森\N{\rENG}I can call ya Madison, if ya like.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.22,0:44:38.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,只要你喜欢，怎么叫都行\N{\rENG}You can call me whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.39,0:44:40.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是我的皇后\N{\rENG}I'll call you queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.43,0:44:47.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,有什么不对吗？\N{\rENG}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.64,0:44:52.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们要有孩子了\N{\rENG}We're gonna have a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.54,0:44:56.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,孩子？\N{\rENG}A baby?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.25,0:45:02.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,你肯定？\N{\rENG}You sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.25,0:45:11.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,你疯了？\N{\rENG}You mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.92,0:45:14.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,疯了？\N{\rENG}Mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.36,0:45:16.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\rENG}No. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.26,0:45:20.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我没疯\N{\rENG}I ain't mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.95,0:45:40.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,作为仆人的眼睛\N{\rENG}"...as the eyes of the servants
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.55,0:45:43.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,看向他们主人的双手\N{\rENG}"look unto the hand of their masters
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.12,0:45:44.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,女仆的眼睛\N{\rENG}"and the eyes of a maid
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.29,0:45:46.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,看向她主人的双手\N{\rENG}"look unto the hand of her mistress..."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.97,0:45:58.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,诺亚醒了酒\N{\rENG}"...and Noah awoke from his wine
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.64,0:46:01.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,知道了小儿子向他所做的事\N{\rENG}"and knew what his youngest son had done unto him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.98,0:46:04.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,他说到，迦南该受诅咒\N{\rENG}<i> "And he said,</i> <i> 'cursed be canaan.'"</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.29,0:46:18.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,必给他弟兄做奴仆的奴仆\N{\rENG}"...servant of servants shall he be unto his brethren.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.62,0:46:20.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,他说到，我们在天上的父神\N{\rENG}"And he said, blessed be the lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.76,0:46:23.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,耶和华闪的神 愿迦南\N{\rENG}<i> "god of shem, and canaan..."</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.39,0:46:51.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,等在这\N{\rENG}Wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.57,0:47:08.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,我去后面看下\N{\rENG}I'll go check 'round back.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.41,0:47:10.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}Yessum.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.83,0:47:33.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,你在我地盘干什么？\N{\rENG}Whatcha doin' on my land?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.47,0:47:35.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨，叫你的狗走开\N{\rENG}Hey! Call off your dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.20,0:47:36.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,你在我地盘干什么？\N{\rENG}Whatcha doin' on my land?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.30,0:47:37.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要，他和我一起的\N{\rENG}No! He's with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.10,0:47:40.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,你他妈是谁？\N{\rENG}Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.74,0:47:44.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是萨缪尔特纳，沃尔索尔教士派我们来的\N{\rENG}I'm Samuel Turner. Reverend walthall sent us.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.21,0:47:46.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个伙计和一个黑鬼牧师\N{\rENG}Fella with the nigger preacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.31,0:47:49.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,来吧\N{\rENG}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.08,0:47:50.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们去找厄尔\N{\rENG}Let's go find Earl.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.49,0:47:57.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,你还好吗？\N{\rENG}You all right? Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.26,0:47:59.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这黑鬼就是黑鬼\N{\rENG}Niggers is niggers here.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.76,0:48:03.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们不会把他们当成其它人来对待\N{\rENG}Now, we don't treat none no different than another.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.60,0:48:05.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们这有规矩\N{\rENG}We got rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.47,0:48:07.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,偷窃，财产损失\N{\rENG}Cost of breakin' 'em, stealin', sassin',
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.80,0:48:09.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,或者其它我和厄尔能想到的事情\N{\rENG}or any other thing that Earl and I think
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.74,0:48:12.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,任何的损失我们都会让他们遭到皮肉之苦\N{\rENG}worth dealin' with, will be paid for in skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.64,0:48:15.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,你要是干涉\N{\rENG}You interfere with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.48,0:48:17.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们会向你开枪\N{\rENG}we'll shoot you where you stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.81,0:48:19.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有问题吗？\N{\rENG}Got any problem with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.30,0:48:22.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,你也可以不干，从哪来回哪去\N{\rENG}you can stop right now and go on back where you came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.89,0:48:29.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,快点\N{\rENG}Come on now! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.66,0:48:32.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,厄尔\N{\rENG}Earl!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.39,0:48:34.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是萨姆 特纳\N{\rENG}This here is Sam Turner,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.36,0:48:36.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有个黑鬼牧师\N{\rENG}fella with the nigger preacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.83,0:48:42.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,你说你从哪里来的？\N{\rENG}Where you say you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.37,0:48:44.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,南安普顿乡\N{\rENG}We from here. Southampton county.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.67,0:48:45.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,就在诺托韦的南面\N{\rENG}Just south of nottoway.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.91,0:48:47.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.31,0:48:49.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,罗塔 扬基 让他们走\N{\rENG}Lotta Yankees makin' their way down that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.28,0:48:52.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,暴民们正在对我们的人生进行破坏\N{\rENG}Rabble-rousin', stirring shit on our way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.41,0:48:55.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,出同样问题了\N{\rENG}They're pullin' that same shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.28,0:48:57.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,厄尔，有个小麻烦\N{\rENG}Earl. Got a little problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.53,0:49:17.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,那个？这个\N{\rENG}Which one? This one.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.70,0:49:19.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,多久了？\N{\rENG}How long?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.41,0:49:22.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,大概一天左右\N{\rENG}Mmm. About a day or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.31,0:49:28.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不吃饭？\N{\rENG}You ain't gonna eat, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.32,0:49:33.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不吃饭，来吧\N{\rENG}You gonna eat? Come on. You ain't gonna eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.89,0:49:36.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯？\N{\rENG}Hmm? Hmm? Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.42,0:49:38.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.86,0:49:41.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个不行，那就用另外的办法了\N{\rENG}If it ain't one thing, it's another.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.75,0:50:05.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,你肯定疑惑我们为什么要用你黑鬼？\N{\rENG}You wonderin' why we could use that nigger of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.38,0:50:07.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,张开他的嘴\N{\rENG}You're seein' it firsthand. All right, get his mouth open.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.22,0:50:11.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，美国佬\N{\rENG}Well, if it ain't the yanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.49,0:50:14.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,是干旱\N{\rENG}...it's the drought.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.49,0:50:16.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果不是干旱\N{\rENG}If not the drought...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.90,0:50:20.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,是这该死的叛乱\N{\rENG}...it's goddamn mutiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.40,0:50:26.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,把漏斗放这\N{\rENG}Get a funnel in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.62,0:50:46.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,即便是黑鬼们所惧怕\N{\rENG}Truth is, even the meanest nigger's
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.96,0:50:49.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,的那些福音\N{\rENG}fearful of the gospel.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.63,0:50:52.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,从你的人嘴说出来也是最美好的话语\N{\rENG}Maybe a good word from your boy there,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.63,0:50:56.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,这些话要比我的手枪更有用\N{\rENG}discipline word,go a lot furtherthan my pistol would.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.94,0:50:58.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,纳特是个好牧师\N{\rENG}Nat's a good preacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.94,0:51:02.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,我才不关心他的好坏\N{\rENG}I don't right care how good he is,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.28,0:51:04.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,关键是他支持什么\N{\rENG}long as he say what he's supposed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.44,0:51:33.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,弟兄们\N{\rENG}Brethren.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.71,0:51:40.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,我向上祈祷你们的罪过\N{\rENG}I pray you sing to the lord
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.31,0:51:44.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们的罪过\N{\rENG}a new song.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.45,0:51:53.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,歌颂义人在会中\N{\rENG}Sing praise in assembly of the righteous.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.86,0:51:57.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,愿圣民因所得的荣耀高兴\N{\rENG}Let the saints be joyful in glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.90,0:52:00.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,让他们大声歌唱\N{\rENG}Let them sing aloud on their beds.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.87,0:52:01.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,高声赞美主\N{\rENG}Let the high praise of god
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.97,0:52:03.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,通过我们圣徒的口\N{\rENG}be on the mouths of the saints,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.50,0:52:05.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们手中握着双刃剑\N{\rENG}and a two-edge sword in their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.34,0:52:07.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,要斩断恶魔家园的复仇之火\N{\rENG}to execute vengeance on the demonic nations,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.84,0:52:09.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,还要惩罚那些\N{\rENG}and punishmenton those peoples
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.51,0:52:11.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,束缚住他们国王双眼\N{\rENG}to bind their kingswith chains
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.44,0:52:13.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,用枷锁捆绑住他们贵族的人们\N{\rENG}and their nobleswith fetters of iron
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.71,0:52:15.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,去斩断他们，给予他们公正的审判\N{\rENG}to execute on them this written judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.88,0:52:17.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,荣誉属于他所有的圣徒\N{\rENG}This honor hath all his saints!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.88,0:52:19.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,赞美主\N{\rENG}Praise the lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.12,0:52:24.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,赞美主，歌颂他吧\N{\rENG}Praise the lord! Sing to him a new song!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.02,0:52:27.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,赞美主\N{\rENG}Praise the lord! Praise the lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.55,0:52:58.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要想着穿这漂亮\N{\rENG}Don't suppose you got a pass anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.49,0:53:00.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,裙子到处乱走\N{\rENG}underneath that pretty dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.39,0:53:02.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有，先生\N{\rENG}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.01,0:53:05.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是有主人的，这儿是他的私人领地\N{\rENG}I belongs to massa guiles and this here his property.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.66,0:53:07.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,你骗我？\N{\rENG}You sassin' me, girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.53,0:53:09.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\rENG}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.40,0:53:11.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,任何人都知道州法律的规定\N{\rENG}Anybody that knows nothin' knows that state law says
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.64,0:53:14.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,法律规定如果一个黑人出现在小于树木线十步的地方\N{\rENG}that if a nigger's less than 10 paces from a tree line,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.84,0:53:16.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,那这个黑人需要通行证\N{\rENG}that nigger need a pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.68,0:53:20.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，先生，我可以拿到的\N{\rENG}Well, sir, I can get one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.95,0:53:23.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,你无处可去\N{\rENG}You ain't goin' nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.68,0:53:25.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,要么你给我看通行证\N{\rENG}Either you gonna show me a pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.85,0:53:27.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,要不你给我看些其它的\N{\rENG}or you gonna show me somethin' else.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.06,0:53:34.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么？\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.09,0:53:35.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,抱歉打扰了\N{\rENG}I'm sorry to disturb ya,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.69,0:53:37.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是纳特有事对你说\N{\rENG}but nat's gotta talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.80,0:53:39.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,发生了些可怕的事情\N{\rENG}Somethin' awful had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.97,0:53:41.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,不管什么情况，告诉他\N{\rENG}Whatever it is, just tell him
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.10,0:53:42.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,我早上会来这\N{\rENG}I'll get to it in the mornin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.97,0:53:45.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,主人，如果你能抽点时间\N{\rENG}Massa, if you could just see nat
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.87,0:53:47.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,见下纳特\N{\rENG}for just a moment, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.47,0:53:49.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,见鬼了，艾塞亚\N{\rENG}Goddamnit, Isaiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.71,0:53:54.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,好了，告诉他我会在前面走廊那见他\N{\rENG}All right, tell him I'll meet him on the front porch.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.85,0:53:57.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就在这，先生\N{\rENG}I'm right here, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.82,0:53:59.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,进来吧\N{\rENG}Might as well come in then.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.95,0:54:05.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,先生，我对此十分抱歉\N{\rENG}Sir, I am awfully sorry about all this. I...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.46,0:54:06.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么情况，纳特？\N{\rENG}What is it, nat?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.59,0:54:09.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,是切瑞，她受了很重的伤\N{\rENG}Cherry... she's been hurt real bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.90,0:54:12.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么伤？\N{\rENG}Whatcha mean hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.00,0:54:15.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,几个人，先生\N{\rENG}A group of men, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.47,0:54:22.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,艾塞亚，给我拿些纸来\N{\rENG}Isaiah, fetch me some paper. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.01,0:54:27.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，你下来吧\N{\rENG}All right, you should go down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.15,0:54:30.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,带上朱庇特，但不要惹麻烦\N{\rENG}Take Jupiter, but don't start no trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.02,0:54:33.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,呆一晚上，早上回来开始做事\N{\rENG}Stay the night, come back first thing in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.05,0:54:36.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，先生，谢谢了\N{\rENG}Yes, sir. Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.68,0:55:00.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,上帝会惩罚那些人的\N{\rENG}God's gonna punish whoever did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.05,0:55:02.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,禽兽\N{\rENG}Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.58,0:56:06.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,纳特？\N{\rENG}Nat?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.08,0:56:07.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在这\N{\rENG}I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.75,0:56:09.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在这\N{\rENG}I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.12,0:56:14.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,是我\N{\rENG}It's me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.59,0:56:17.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在这\N{\rENG}I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.69,0:56:21.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,对不起\N{\rENG}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.96,0:56:26.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要，不需要道歉\N{\rENG}No, no. You don't apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.27,0:56:28.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不要责怪自己\N{\rENG}You don't owe that to nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.97,0:56:36.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,告诉我是谁干的\N{\rENG}You need to tell me who done this to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.14,0:56:38.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,我会处理的，你听见吗？\N{\rENG}'Cause I'm gonna take care of it, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.78,0:56:41.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的神啊\N{\rENG}On my soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.62,0:56:47.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,我需要你的指引\N{\rENG}I need you to tell me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.81,0:57:18.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,收刀入鞘吧\N{\rENG}"Put up again thy sword into his place.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.18,0:57:24.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,凡动刀的\N{\rENG}"For all they that take the sword
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.36,0:57:27.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,必死在刀下\N{\rENG}"shall pass with the sword."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.83,0:57:32.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,你曾经教过我\N{\rENG}You taught me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.84,0:57:39.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,我需要你\N{\rENG}I need you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.04,0:57:44.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,乔安娜也需要\N{\rENG}Joanna, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.84,0:57:49.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,把这个留给上帝\N{\rENG}Leave this to the lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.93,0:58:07.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,你要见我，先生？\N{\rENG}You wanted to see me, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.97,0:58:13.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，切瑞怎么样了？\N{\rENG}Yeah. How's cherry?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.97,0:58:15.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我相信她会好起来的\N{\rENG}I'm believin' she'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.84,0:58:17.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,那就好\N{\rENG}Good. Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.38,0:58:22.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我还能做些什么\N{\rENG}Not many woulda let you go like I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.01,0:58:23.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rENG}Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.85,0:58:24.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.12,0:58:27.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们今晚有个重要的活动\N{\rENG}We're having a big get-together tonight
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.85,0:58:29.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,有很多重要人物出席\N{\rENG}with a lot of very important people.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.89,0:58:32.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,自从我父亲去世后就没有这样过\N{\rENG}Kind of like when daddy was alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.73,0:58:34.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我需要你，还要几个人在这帮忙\N{\rENG}So I'm gonna need you and a couple of others in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.99,0:58:36.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有谁能\N{\rENG}Anyone who's had experience
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.46,0:58:39.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,懂礼貌，服务好，有经验的\N{\rENG}servin' and being respectable help.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.70,0:58:40.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,明白，先生\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.80,0:58:44.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,能告诉我对您来说这些客人有多重要吗？\N{\rENG}Can't tell ya how important this is for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.07,0:58:45.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果我们做的好\N{\rENG}If we get this right,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.31,0:58:47.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,那么意味着特纳的姓氏会再次崛起\N{\rENG}the Turner name will mean something again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.74,0:58:52.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,以赛亚\N{\rENG}Isaiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.85,0:58:55.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,是，先生\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.13,0:59:48.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像你知道那样，这次年度晚宴\N{\rENG}As you all know, this annual dinner
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.20,0:59:50.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,是我们的父亲多年来的传统\N{\rENG}was a tradition of our daddy many years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.44,0:59:53.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,在他所有的崇尚中，家庭地位，信念\N{\rENG}And for all he believed, he placed family, faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.51,0:59:55.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,传统是他最为看重的东西\N{\rENG}and tradition at the top of his priority list.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.91,0:59:57.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,二十年后\N{\rENG}Twenty years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.28,1:00:00.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们的财富正是因为有了这些相同的优先等级而得以保持\N{\rENG}those same priorities have kept this property afloat.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.18,1:00:02.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,那个和即期付款都是从你这个黑人牧师那来的\N{\rENG}That and the cash down from your colored preacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.45,1:00:05.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,对的\N{\rENG}Yeah! That, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.42,1:00:07.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,希望上帝可以世世代代\N{\rENG}May god continue to bless all of us
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.89,1:00:09.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,不停的祝福我们\N{\rENG}for many generations to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.99,1:00:13.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,对的\N{\rENG}Hear, hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.16,1:00:14.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,纳特，你可以带我们一起祷告吗？\N{\rENG}Nat, would you please lead us in prayer?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.99,1:00:16.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,尊敬的教士，我相信你不会介意的\N{\rENG}Reverend, I trust you wouldn't mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.53,1:00:18.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想不会\N{\rENG}I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.01,1:00:32.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,天父\N{\rENG}Heavenly father.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.34,1:00:36.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们前来感谢你的言行\N{\rENG}We come to thank you for your word and your will.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.18,1:00:40.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们祈祷并且感谢你\N{\rENG}We pray for and thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.29,1:00:44.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,为了你的保护与承诺\N{\rENG}for your protection and your promise.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.19,1:00:46.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们将顺从与你\N{\rENG}And in our obedience,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.56,1:00:50.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,你的敌人也将是我们的敌人\N{\rENG}you will be an enemy to our enemies.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.50,1:00:54.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们将反抗你所反抗的\N{\rENG}That you will oppose those who oppose us.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.50,1:01:01.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,继续指引着我们，我的主啊\N{\rENG}Continue to guide us, o lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.04,1:01:04.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们将继续跟随着你\N{\rENG}and we will continue to follow.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.21,1:01:06.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,穿越磨难，勇往直前\N{\rENG}Through fine tribulation we will push forward,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.88,1:01:11.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,认识到只有你才能作为我们的力量和源泉\N{\rENG}recognizing only you as our source and strength.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.88,1:01:16.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们将呼唤着你神圣的名字\N{\rENG}In your holy name we pray.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.05,1:01:18.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,阿门\N{\rENG}Amen.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.06,1:01:20.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,魔幻厨房\N{\rENG}Bon appetit.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.96,1:01:22.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,父亲总是说\N{\rENG}Daddy always said,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.36,1:01:25.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,三个黑胡椒放在一杯\N{\rENG}"three black peppercorns in a glass of port,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.06,1:01:28.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是最好的餐后酒\N{\rENG}"and you got yourself a excellent digestif."
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.40,1:01:30.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,不错，黑色总是引入入胜\N{\rENG}Well, black is always tasty.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.57,1:01:36.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,特别是那块肉，多汁，甜美\N{\rENG}Especially a nice piece of black meat. Sweet. Juicy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.50,1:01:38.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不干，好吗？\N{\rENG}I ain't doin' it, all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.48,1:01:41.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我需要你离开这\N{\rENG}Naw, naw. I need you to get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.25,1:01:45.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,办不到，你才刚一露面\N{\rENG}Ain't gonna happen, man. You just come out here...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.55,1:01:48.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨，嗨，嗨\N{\rENG}Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey! Ho, ho, ho!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.39,1:01:50.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,出什么事了？\N{\rENG}What's goin' on, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.42,1:01:51.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我不同意  - 嗯？\N{\rENG}- I ain't doin' it.  - Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.66,1:01:53.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我不同意，纳特  - 什么情况？\N{\rENG}- I ain't doin' it, nat.  - Doin' what?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.59,1:01:55.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们要先对我用私刑\N{\rENG}He'd have to lynch me first.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.43,1:01:57.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,私刑？我们在讨论什么东西？\N{\rENG}Lynch ya? What are we talkin' about?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.53,1:02:02.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个萨缪尔先生的客人\N{\rENG}One of Samuel's guests...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.30,1:02:05.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么？\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.10,1:02:11.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个客人要求伊森\N{\rENG}One of Samuel's guests requested Esther, and, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.12,1:02:20.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,去找萨缪尔先生，告诉他发生了什么\N{\rENG}Just go and talk to Samuel. Just tell him what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.65,1:02:22.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,告诉他，他会作出正确决定的\N{\rENG}Tell him what it was and he'll straighten this out.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.55,1:02:26.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,但这是萨缪尔先生亲自派我来的\N{\rENG}But Samuel sent me over here personally, nat.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.12,1:02:30.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不能这么做，纳特\N{\rENG}I can't do it, nat. I won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.30,1:02:32.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,汉克兄弟\N{\rENG}Brother hark...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.06,1:02:33.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是谁？\N{\rENG}But, what... Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.53,1:02:35.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,汉克兄弟，你觉得\N{\rENG}Brother hark, do you think
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.13,1:02:38.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想为这个过来吗？\N{\rENG}that I wanna come over here for this?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.40,1:02:40.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,你听见了？\N{\rENG}You here, ain't ya?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.44,1:02:43.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,纳特\N{\rENG}Nat!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.35,1:02:45.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,她在哪里？\N{\rENG}Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.41,1:02:49.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,萨缪尔，先生，请不要这样做\N{\rENG}Samuel, sir. Please, you can't do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.08,1:02:55.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,都还好吗？\N{\rENG}Everything all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.02,1:02:56.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,都还行\N{\rENG}Oh, it's just fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.99,1:02:58.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,我会径直走进去的\N{\rENG}I'll be inside directly.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.59,1:03:00.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,希望你不要孤单\N{\rENG}I hope you won't be alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.33,1:03:05.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我保证你不会的\N{\rENG}I assure you, i will not be.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.33,1:03:07.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你把这个搞的一团糟，我发誓\N{\rENG}If you mess this up for me, my hand to god,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.70,1:03:10.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我会在第二天让你体无完肤\N{\rENG}I will lynch every one of you come mornin!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.00,1:03:11.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,你明白我吗？\N{\rENG}Do you understand me?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.50,1:03:14.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,把她带来\N{\rENG}Fetch her.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.64,1:03:15.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,是，先生\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.70,1:04:15.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,没关系的\N{\rENG}It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.71,1:04:34.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,他在那，纳特，神在哪？\N{\rENG}Where is he, nat? Where's god now?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.10,1:04:46.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,汉克\N{\rENG}Hark.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.11,1:04:57.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,对不起\N{\rENG}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.74,1:05:01.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在找一个叫纳特的牧师\N{\rENG}I'm looking for a preacher named nat.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.85,1:05:03.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为他的罪过\N{\rENG}He's been banned from every church
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.25,1:05:05.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,他被这个国家的所有教堂都禁止出现了\N{\rENG}in the county for his sins.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.01,1:05:07.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,对于他所做的事情，他已经是很幸运的了\N{\rENG}He's lucky that's all he got for what he done.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.19,1:05:10.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,世间对于不道德的交易有它自己的处理方式\N{\rENG}The world has its way with dealing with the immoral.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.12,1:05:12.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,重要的是谁来衡量发生\N{\rENG}Above all those who cast that immorality
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.52,1:05:15.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,在他身上与孩子的这些不道德行为\N{\rENG}on the children as he has.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.29,1:05:19.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是我们所有人都是有罪的，伊丽莎白小姐\N{\rENG}But no one is without sin, miss Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.13,1:05:22.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个男人需要忏悔，而且需要被指引\N{\rENG}And this man wants to repent and be delivered.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.13,1:05:26.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,做为上帝的牧羊人，这是我的职责\N{\rENG}As a Shepherd of the lord, it's my duty to serve.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.81,1:05:28.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以\N{\rENG}So...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.77,1:05:32.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想要为他洗礼\N{\rENG}I'd like to baptize him.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.64,1:05:33.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,见你的鬼\N{\rENG}The hell you will!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.71,1:05:35.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,杰斯罗，注意你的言辞\N{\rENG}Jethro, you will mind your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.35,1:05:36.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很抱歉，伊丽莎白小姐\N{\rENG}With respect, miss Elizabeth,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.58,1:05:38.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,黑人不能为白人洗礼\N{\rENG}a nigger can't baptize no white man.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.35,1:05:42.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是认为我们应该等萨缪尔先生回来\N{\rENG}I just think we should wait for Mr. Samuel to get back.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.71,1:05:44.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,杰斯罗，去前院等着\N{\rENG}Jethro, go wait in the front yard.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.41,1:05:46.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,萨缪尔先生回来前有我们在\N{\rENG}Mr. Samuel gets back, he'll have both of us!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.29,1:05:48.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不会再说第二遍了\N{\rENG}I won't ask you again.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.16,1:05:53.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,你等着\N{\rENG}Boy, you gonna get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.43,1:05:59.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,你确定你要这么做吗，纳特？\N{\rENG}Are you sure you want to do this, nat?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.34,1:06:01.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,萨缪尔不会喜欢这样做的\N{\rENG}Samuel may not like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.51,1:06:04.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在有很多白人围在这附近\N{\rENG}Nor will a lot of other folks around here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.34,1:06:07.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要考虑太多了，夫人\N{\rENG}Don't got too much choice, missus.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.81,1:06:11.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个人依然属于神\N{\rENG}This man still belongs to god.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.18,1:06:14.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,当你站在了上帝与它的子民之间\N{\rENG}When you stand between the lord and his people,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.35,1:06:16.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,这会是个危险的境地\N{\rENG}it's a dangerous place to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.41,1:07:20.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们全家对你一直够好的\N{\rENG}We've been good to you. My whole family has.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.59,1:07:23.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,你就是这样回报我的\N{\rENG}And you go on and do something like this to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.76,1:07:27.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,一个黑人为一个白人洗礼，还是在我的地盘上\N{\rENG}A nigger baptizing a white man on my property!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.76,1:07:29.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道这让我们看上去像什么吗？\N{\rENG}Do you know how this makes us look?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.59,1:07:33.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,这会毁了我们所做的一切\N{\rENG}This could ruin everything we worked for!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.40,1:07:36.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,伙计，你最好快点解释下\N{\rENG}Boy, you better say something and quick!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.60,1:07:40.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,圣灵立你们作为全群的监督\N{\rENG}"Take heed therefore unto yourselves,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.27,1:07:41.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们就当为自己谨慎\N{\rENG}"and to all the flock over which
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.51,1:07:43.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,也为全群谨慎\N{\rENG}"the holy ghost hath made you overseers.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.78,1:07:45.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,牧养神的教会\N{\rENG}"To feed the church of god
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.38,1:07:48.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是他用自己的血所买来的\N{\rENG}"which he has purchased with his own blood."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.35,1:07:50.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,劝…\N{\rENG}Ex...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.45,1:07:52.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,劝戒仆人\N{\rENG}"Exhort servants
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.32,1:07:55.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,要顺服自己的主人\N{\rENG}"to be obedient to thy own masters,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.45,1:07:56.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,凡事讨他的喜欢\N{\rENG}"and to please them well
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.79,1:07:58.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,不可顶撞他\N{\rENG}"in all things not answering again..."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.01,1:08:01.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是被买来的不要成为人的奴仆\N{\rENG}"You were bought with a price, do not become slaves of men."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.63,1:08:04.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,他会亵渎对抗圣灵\N{\rENG}"He that shall blaspheme against the holy ghost
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.53,1:08:07.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,永远不会被原谅，但是非常危险\N{\rENG}"hath never forgiveness, but is in danger..."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.33,1:08:08.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,要防备假先知\N{\rENG}"Beware of false prophets
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.73,1:08:10.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是那个披着羊皮的\N{\rENG}"who come dressed in sheep's clothing,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.30,1:08:11.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是内心确是贪婪饥饿的狼\N{\rENG}"but inwardly are ravening wolves!"
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.87,1:08:13.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,你个黑杂种，纳特\N{\rENG}You black bastard! Nat!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.61,1:08:14.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,他的秘密出卖了他\N{\rENG}"He that stealeth a man and selleth him..."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.81,1:08:15.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要盯着我\N{\rENG}Don't you eyeball me, boy!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.81,1:08:17.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,或是如果他被发现在他的手里，他应该坚定无疑\N{\rENG}"...or if he be found in his hand, he shall surely
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.38,1:08:18.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,被处以死刑\N{\rENG}"be put to death!"
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.32,1:08:30.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,拉他去公示栏\N{\rENG}Get him to the post.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.89,1:09:40.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨，伙计\N{\rENG}Hey, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.39,1:09:47.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你活着熬过来了\N{\rENG}If you make it out of this alive,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.40,1:09:51.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要让你日子更难过\N{\rENG}I'm gonna ride you harder than hogs on slop.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.04,1:09:57.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,去死吧\N{\rENG}Die.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.04,1:12:15.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,吸取教训了吗\N{\rENG}You learned your lesson, boy?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.55,1:12:21.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，先生，我学到了\N{\rENG}Oh, yes, sir, I've learned.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.79,1:12:23.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,把他放下来\N{\rENG}Go on, get him off.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.76,1:12:30.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,你完成布道有段时间了\N{\rENG}You're done preachin' for a little while.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.90,1:12:32.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也不喜欢你和其它组成员去到处瞎跑了\N{\rENG}And I don't want you runnin' off with any groups,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.90,1:12:35.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,除非我和杰斯罗在的情况下，明白吗？\N{\rENG}unless me and Jethro are there, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.73,1:12:38.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,是，先生\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.17,1:12:40.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，去把自己弄干净些\N{\rENG}All right, go and get yourself cleaned up.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.24,1:12:42.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,回田里工作吧\N{\rENG}Be back in the field come morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.82,1:13:00.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,兄弟，你还好吗？\N{\rENG}Brother, you all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.23,1:13:05.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨，嗨\N{\rENG}Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.04,1:13:22.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,我看着你的祖父去世\N{\rENG}I watched your grandfather die
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.75,1:13:25.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,在老地方\N{\rENG}in old land.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.88,1:13:30.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,亲眼看着他的灵魂升天\N{\rENG}Saw him give up the ghost with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.19,1:13:34.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,他看着我\N{\rENG}And he saw me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.23,1:13:37.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,他的灵魂在那天得到了升华\N{\rENG}He harnessed the holy spirit that day.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.03,1:13:39.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes, he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.90,1:13:41.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我感到很自豪\N{\rENG}I was proud of him.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.20,1:13:45.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,非常自豪\N{\rENG}So proud.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.84,1:13:47.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,我依旧感谢着神灵\N{\rENG}I still thank god
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.77,1:13:52.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,就在他死的那天\N{\rENG}that he died that day.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.91,1:13:56.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,他没有活着看见这些，而我看见了\N{\rENG}That he didn't live to see the things I seen.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.72,1:14:03.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,看着一个坚强的人被打倒\N{\rENG}To watch a strong man broken down
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.39,1:14:08.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,被一些可怕的事情\N{\rENG}is a terrible thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.23,1:14:45.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨，奶奶\N{\rENG}Hey, Nana.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.70,1:14:54.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,伤口缝合的还不错\N{\rENG}The stitches held up good.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.28,1:15:09.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,奶奶\N{\rENG}Nana?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.45,1:16:13.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,你还好吗？\N{\rENG}You all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.22,1:16:22.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,最主要的\N{\rENG}Mostly.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.07,1:16:35.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,我需要你聚集一些你信得过的人\N{\rENG}I need you to round up a few men you trust.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.47,1:16:37.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,让他们与我们在柏树林那见面\N{\rENG}Have them meet us at the big cypress
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.14,1:16:39.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,就在小屋池塘那后天晚上\N{\rENG}at cabin pond night after next.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.25,1:16:44.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,哈克\N{\rENG}Hark.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.85,1:16:47.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,他还在这，兄弟\N{\rENG}He's still here, brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.55,1:16:51.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,尽管这样\N{\rENG}Even now.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.51,1:17:12.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是西蒙\N{\rENG}This is Simon.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.11,1:17:14.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,萨缪尔回来一个月后买了他，在诺福克\N{\rENG}Samuel bought him a month back in Norfolk.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.91,1:17:16.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我记得，欢迎，兄弟\N{\rENG}I remember. Welcome, brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.91,1:17:18.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,你认识尼尔森\N{\rENG}And you know Nelson.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.28,1:17:20.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,欢迎\N{\rENG}Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.99,1:17:22.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是威尔\N{\rENG}This is will.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.29,1:17:26.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,世界变化真快，欢迎\N{\rENG}Word travels fast. Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.52,1:17:30.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨，这是大人们的事情，走开了\N{\rENG}Hey! This grown folk's business! Get! Get!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.46,1:17:32.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,慢点\N{\rENG}Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.13,1:17:34.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,过来这\N{\rENG}Come on over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.14,1:17:41.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,从兰德尔来的？是，先生\N{\rENG}Come from Randall's? Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.44,1:17:43.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,他还是个孩子\N{\rENG}He's just a boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.14,1:17:44.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,大卫也是\N{\rENG}So was David.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.21,1:17:48.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,来吧，坐下\N{\rENG}Come on. Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.02,1:18:03.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我已经追随了上帝很长时间了\N{\rENG}I've been following the lord a long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.16,1:18:07.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,布道，引用圣经\N{\rENG}Preachin', citing scripture,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.03,1:18:09.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,从几页篇章里分享福音\N{\rENG}sharing the gospel from the few pages
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.57,1:18:11.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,而且我也认同里面的部分内容\N{\rENG}and sections I've been allowed.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.60,1:18:14.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是回到这个现实世界，所有这一切\N{\rENG}But I've gone back through this word, all of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.91,1:18:17.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,用一种新的方式来看待的话\N{\rENG}With new eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.04,1:18:18.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,在我现在看来，这些诗篇\N{\rENG}I see now, for every verse
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.91,1:18:20.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,都是他们用来作为奴役我们枷锁\N{\rENG}they use to support our bondage,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.44,1:18:22.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们的自由在这看起来是一种苛求\N{\rENG}there's another demanding our freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.61,1:18:27.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,每一个篇章都被他们证明现在对我们的这些折磨是合理依法的\N{\rENG}Every verse they use to justify our torture,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.05,1:18:30.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,而这些奴隶主的行为也不会轻易被下地狱\N{\rENG}there's another damning them to hell for those actions.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.02,1:18:35.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,上帝告诉我，接下去我们要开拓眼界\N{\rENG}Lord has spoken to me. Visions of what's to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.99,1:18:38.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,要用善良来对抗邪恶\N{\rENG}A rise of good against evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.53,1:18:42.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,有人想做首先，他必做众人末后\N{\rENG}The first shall be last, and the last shall be first.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.00,1:18:48.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,兄弟们，我们是被选中的\N{\rENG}Brothers, we've been chosen.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.47,1:18:50.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们要干什么？\N{\rENG}What are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.41,1:18:52.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,做大卫和基甸\N{\rENG}Same as David and Gideon
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.38,1:18:56.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,约书亚和参孙\N{\rENG}and Joshua and Samson.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.71,1:18:59.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们要战斗，就我们六个人？\N{\rENG}We'll fight. The six of us?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.02,1:19:01.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,开始是这样，但是一旦开始了\N{\rENG}At first. But once it begins,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.12,1:19:02.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们兄弟姐妹就会加入\N{\rENG}our brothers and sisters will join.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.52,1:19:04.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,这儿可是有很多白人的\N{\rENG}There's a whole lot of whites.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.12,1:19:05.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这个国家有多少奴隶？\N{\rENG}How many slaves you think there are in the county?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.96,1:19:09.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有的种植园里有多少？白人又有多少？\N{\rENG}On all the plantations? How many whites?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.56,1:19:11.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是他们有枪\N{\rENG}But they got guns.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.03,1:19:12.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们将夺取耶路撒冷的军火库\N{\rENG}We'll take the armory in Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.40,1:19:14.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们也会有枪的\N{\rENG}We'll have guns, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.13,1:19:15.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,耶路撒冷？\N{\rENG}Jerusalem?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.73,1:19:18.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,对的，就在北方十英里的地方\N{\rENG}That's right. It's only 10 miles north.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.37,1:19:19.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们就从特纳这里开始\N{\rENG}We'll start right here at Turner's
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.67,1:19:21.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,打出我们自己的天下\N{\rENG}and fight our way there.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.24,1:19:23.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,到时我们就有几百人\N{\rENG}By then we'll number in the hundreds,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.11,1:19:25.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,甚至上千人\N{\rENG}thousands even.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.04,1:19:27.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,星星之火可以燎原\N{\rENG}The grapevine's ablaze with talks of fightin'.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.75,1:19:30.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,奴隶制结束了\N{\rENG}Slaves all over havin' meetins'.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.31,1:19:32.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们在等待\N{\rENG}They waitin' on something.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.25,1:19:33.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,等我们的召唤\N{\rENG}They waitin' on us.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.05,1:19:38.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们在富勒的地方停留\N{\rENG}We make a stop at Fowler place?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.42,1:19:40.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,可以\N{\rENG}We will.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.09,1:19:44.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,我加入\N{\rENG}I'm with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.30,1:19:45.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,我也是\N{\rENG}Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.53,1:19:47.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我们什么时候战斗？ - 很快\N{\rENG}- When we fight?  - Soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.50,1:19:49.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,上帝会给我启示的\N{\rENG}The lord will give us a sign.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.77,1:19:51.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这之前我们要保持坚定\N{\rENG}Until then we remain steadfast,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.44,1:19:54.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,做好准备等待上帝的召唤\N{\rENG}ready to strike at the moment of the lord's call.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.27,1:19:56.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,带着我们强大的信念\N{\rENG}With the strength of our father,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.17,1:19:57.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们会最终获胜的\N{\rENG}we'll cut the head from the serpent.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.74,1:20:01.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们会全部摧毁他们\N{\rENG}We'll destroy them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.81,1:20:32.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,有什么不对吗？\N{\rENG}Somethin' wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.51,1:20:36.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,前几天晚上有个会议\N{\rENG}There was a meeting a few nights ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.18,1:20:38.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,虽然我不知道说了些什么\N{\rENG}And although I was not privy to what was said,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.82,1:20:41.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只能靠假设\N{\rENG}I can only assume
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.32,1:20:45.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,秘密不能让太多人知道\N{\rENG}by the secrecy that it was not altogether productive.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.21,1:21:04.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在，我不明白意思\N{\rENG}<i> Now,</i> <i> I don't know what ideas</i>
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.74,1:21:08.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,在你的脑海四周飘荡\N{\rENG}<i> is floatin' around</i> <i> in your head,</i>
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.35,1:21:10.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是我就在你周围，足够了解你\N{\rENG}<i> but I been around here</i> <i> long enough to know</i>
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.58,1:21:12.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,确信无疑的结果\N{\rENG}that the result of certain ideas
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.68,1:21:14.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,不会让你随心所欲的\N{\rENG}is not gonna get you what you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.85,1:21:17.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想要的\N{\rENG}All I want,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.35,1:21:19.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想代表神为了被压迫的人们\N{\rENG}I want for the oppressed people of god.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.52,1:21:22.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,你愿意为他们去死？\N{\rENG}You want death for them?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.39,1:21:24.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,为了你妻子？\N{\rENG}For your wife?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.20,1:21:27.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,为了你女儿？\N{\rENG}For your daughter?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.43,1:21:28.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果这是神的旨意\N{\rENG}If it be god's will.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.70,1:21:30.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,神的旨意\N{\rENG}God's will?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.37,1:21:34.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,谁让你这么坚决\N{\rENG}And who determined you
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.21,1:21:36.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,为了这样的事情而成为一个工具？\N{\rENG}to be the instrument of such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.54,1:21:37.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,他\N{\rENG}He has.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.88,1:21:45.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,你确定\N{\rENG}You just make sure that he's the one doin' the orderin'.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.55,1:21:50.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,神的仆人被称为爱的领路人\N{\rENG}Man of god is called to lead in love.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.55,1:21:53.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有都会离我们而去\N{\rENG}Anything else will leave us all worse off.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.79,1:21:57.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,他是爱的神，纳特\N{\rENG}He is a god of love, nat.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.39,1:21:59.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要忘记了\N{\rENG}Don't you forget that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.90,1:22:01.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不会\N{\rENG}I won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.90,1:22:05.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,我会忘记他是愤怒的神\N{\rENG}Nor will I forget he's a god of wrath.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.58,1:22:18.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,妈妈\N{\rENG}Mmm...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.26,1:22:34.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,上帝在召唤我\N{\rENG}The lord's calling me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.87,1:22:38.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,去战斗\N{\rENG}To stand and fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.91,1:22:52.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道这天终会来到\N{\rENG}I knew this day would come.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.78,1:22:58.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,我告诉自己不要害怕\N{\rENG}I told myself i wouldn't be scared.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.96,1:23:02.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的有生之年\N{\rENG}All my life,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.46,1:23:07.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,都在祈祷上帝能帮助我们\N{\rENG}I've been praying for the lord to help us
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.20,1:23:10.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,或者派个救世主来拯救我们\N{\rENG}or to send someone who could.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.30,1:23:14.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们所有人都这样\N{\rENG}We all have.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.47,1:23:19.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,只是没曾想盼来的确是我丈夫\N{\rENG}Just wasn't expecting it to be my own husband.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.85,1:23:34.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果是上帝召唤你去战斗\N{\rENG}If the lord's called you to fight,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.76,1:23:37.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,你就去\N{\rENG}you fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.83,1:23:41.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,你为我而战\N{\rENG}You fight for me,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.50,1:23:44.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有乔安娜\N{\rENG}and Joanna.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.34,1:23:51.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,为了我们所有人\N{\rENG}You fight for us all.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.91,1:23:52.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯？\N{\rENG}Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.58,1:25:04.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,谁在那？\N{\rENG}Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.59,1:25:11.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,纳特？\N{\rENG}Nat?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.42,1:25:12.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.78,1:25:33.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,等着，他妈的\N{\rENG}Wait, goddamnit!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.08,1:25:39.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,可恶\N{\rENG}Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.91,1:27:18.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,母亲？\N{\rENG}Momma?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.22,1:27:23.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,母亲\N{\rENG}Momma.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.72,1:27:28.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,纳特？哦，上帝，我睡的太晚了\N{\rENG}Nat? Oh lord, i slept too late.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.93,1:27:30.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有，母亲\N{\rENG}No, no... Momma.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.73,1:27:35.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你今天不用干活了\N{\rENG}You won't have to work today.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.73,1:27:37.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,你自由了\N{\rENG}You free.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.74,1:27:48.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,战役开始\N{\rENG}The battle's begun, ma.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.11,1:27:51.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,西蒙\N{\rENG}Simon.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.55,1:27:56.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,西蒙会带你去里斯那里\N{\rENG}Simon will take you to Reese's.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.95,1:27:58.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要你照顾好切瑞和乔安娜\N{\rENG}And I need you to take care of cherry and Joanna
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.86,1:28:00.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,知道我回来，好吗？\N{\rENG}'till I get back, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.96,1:28:04.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么了？\N{\rENG}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.50,1:28:06.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,没事\N{\rENG}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.87,1:28:10.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,我为你自豪\N{\rENG}I'm proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.89,1:28:30.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,你做了什么？\N{\rENG}What did you do, boy? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.52,1:28:32.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,你杀了他们？\N{\rENG}Huh? You killed them, boy?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.79,1:28:34.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,是你干的吗？\N{\rENG}Is that what you did?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.89,1:28:38.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,你杀了他们，你等于杀了我们\N{\rENG}ou kill them and you kill us!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.67,1:28:46.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,你等于杀了我们所有人\N{\rENG}You killed all of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.54,1:28:49.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们死定了\N{\rENG}We already dead. We already dead!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.21,1:28:53.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,你死定了\N{\rENG}You dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.68,1:28:56.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们死定了\N{\rENG}We already dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.68,1:29:02.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们要死了\N{\rENG}We dead now!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.69,1:29:10.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们\N{\rENG}Your
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.56,1:29:13.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,之前的主人已经不在了\N{\rENG}earthly master is gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.70,1:29:18.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们是自由的男人和女人\N{\rENG}You're now free men and women,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.70,1:29:20.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,只服务与上帝\N{\rENG}servants of only the lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.94,1:29:25.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像上帝之剑赦免我们的敌人一样\N{\rENG}As the sword of the lord bears down on our enemies,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.58,1:29:28.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我们的祖先和未出生的孩子高兴吧\N{\rENG}our ancestors and unborn children rejoice.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.68,1:29:31.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们死了吗？\N{\rENG}Are we dead?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.05,1:29:38.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有，我说大家都活着\N{\rENG}No. I say we are now alive,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.72,1:29:40.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,透过这些眼睛看到的\N{\rENG}seeing through eyes that have been denied us
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.69,1:29:43.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,自从出生以来就在受压迫和黑暗的日子里\N{\rENG}since being born into the darkness of bondage.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.20,1:29:47.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,与我们站在一起\N{\rENG}Stand with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.01,1:29:49.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,让你们那些被抓获的兄弟姐妹们\N{\rENG}Let your other captive brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.33,1:29:50.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,也知道自由的滋味\N{\rENG}also know freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.73,1:29:52.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,与我们的孩子在一起\N{\rENG}Stand that our children
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.27,1:29:53.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,让他们世代都知道\N{\rENG}for generations to come will know
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.87,1:29:55.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,神的伟大与奇妙\N{\rENG}that with the supernatural power of god,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.37,1:29:56.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们挺直自己的脊梁\N{\rENG}we straightened our backs
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.74,1:29:58.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,对抗邪恶\N{\rENG}against the works of the evil one!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.01,1:30:03.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,与我们在一起\N{\rENG}Stand with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.73,1:30:59.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,我能自己做吗？\N{\rENG}Can I do this myself?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.86,1:31:59.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,孩子，他走了\N{\rENG}The boy! He gone!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.74,1:32:10.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,呼呼\N{\rENG}Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.03,1:32:31.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,趴下\N{\rENG}Get down!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.23,1:32:35.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨，牧师\N{\rENG}Hey, preacher!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.90,1:32:37.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,汉克\N{\rENG}Hark!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.40,1:32:39.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,你在外面？\N{\rENG}Are you out there?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.40,1:32:41.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,告诉那个人后退\N{\rENG}Tell the men to fall back.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.04,1:32:42.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么？\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.77,1:32:44.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果我们现在发生枪战\N{\rENG}If we have a gun battle now,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.11,1:32:45.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们就永远到不了耶路撒冷\N{\rENG}we'll never make it to Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.31,1:32:46.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,我和我的人准备好了\N{\rENG}Me and my boys is ready!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.41,1:32:47.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要复仇\N{\rENG}I want my revenge!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.78,1:32:49.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,这不是复仇\N{\rENG}This ain't about revenge, hark!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.01,1:32:52.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,你们都要被吊死，你听见了吗？\N{\rENG}You all gonna hang! You hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.12,1:32:53.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有人\N{\rENG}All of ya!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.02,1:32:58.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,祖先\N{\rENG}The root,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.26,1:32:59.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要有分歧\N{\rENG}not the branch.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.79,1:33:03.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们必须保持专注，兄弟\N{\rENG}We must stay focused, brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.06,1:33:08.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,撤退\N{\rENG}Will! Fall back! C'mon! C'mon, y'all. C'mon.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.93,1:33:11.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,让我们撤退\N{\rENG}Let's fall back, y'all!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.83,1:33:37.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,你还好吗？\N{\rENG}You all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.23,1:33:42.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们所有人\N{\rENG}It's all of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.37,1:33:43.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,就这？\N{\rENG}This it?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.12,1:34:05.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,哈克，你觉得现在几点了？\N{\rENG}Hark, what time you think it is?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.12,1:34:09.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,五点三十，五点三十五\N{\rENG}5:30, 5:35.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.06,1:34:12.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,什么？\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.00,1:34:20.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,现在我会两排下来\N{\rENG}By now I'd be two rows down,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.87,1:34:22.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,半袋\N{\rENG}half a bag full.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.41,1:34:25.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,我将前往谷仓\N{\rENG}I'd be headed to the barn,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.34,1:34:27.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,准备喂牲口\N{\rENG}gettin' ready to feed the stock.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.34,1:34:29.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,我要去烟熏室烧开水\N{\rENG}I'd be boiling water in the smokehouse,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.48,1:34:31.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,倒在那些主人的头上\N{\rENG}thinkin' 'bout dumping on massa's head.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.08,1:34:35.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,我将捆绑木桶，填补裂缝\N{\rENG}I'd be tying the barrels, sealin' cracks.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.29,1:34:37.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,记录着树叶与稻草\N{\rENG}Checkin' the leaves and straw.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.42,1:34:40.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,包装和消磨这一切\N{\rENG}Packin' and stackin' 'em up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.52,1:34:43.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,避开爆竹的飞屑\N{\rENG}Dodgin' that cracker's lash.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.30,1:34:48.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,但不是今天\N{\rENG}Not today.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.16,1:34:50.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,对的，先生\N{\rENG}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.17,1:34:52.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是今天\N{\rENG}Not today.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.64,1:34:59.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,去向耶路撒冷？\N{\rENG}On to Jerusalem?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.18,1:35:00.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,去向耶路撒冷？\N{\rENG}On to Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.58,1:35:02.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,去向耶路撒冷？\N{\rENG}On to Jerusalem!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.50,1:35:27.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,好了，接下去你们应该这么办\N{\rENG}All right, this is how this is gonna work.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.24,1:35:30.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,把武器丢在地上\N{\rENG}You're gonna throw the weapons to the ground,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.71,1:35:33.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,接着趴在地上\N{\rENG}then you're gonna lie down.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.05,1:35:37.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,快点\N{\rENG}Do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.51,1:35:42.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,上帝是我们的明灯，是我们的救世主\N{\rENG}The lord is our light and our salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.45,1:35:44.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们应该怕谁？\N{\rENG}Of whom we shall fear?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.42,1:35:48.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,把你们的武器丢在地上\N{\rENG}Throw your weapons to the ground!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.63,1:35:51.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们要相信上帝的强大\N{\rENG}The lord is the strength of our lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.96,1:35:54.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们应该要害怕谁？\N{\rENG}Of whom shall we be afraid?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.63,1:35:59.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,当邪恶，甚至仇敌\N{\rENG}When the wicked, even our enemies
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.37,1:36:00.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有我们的敌人来到面前\N{\rENG}and our foes came upon us
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.74,1:36:03.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,要生吞活剥了我们时，他们只会失败跌倒\N{\rENG}to eat up our flesh, they stumbled and fell!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.51,1:36:05.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,他妈的，黑鬼们\N{\rENG}Goddamn, niggers.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.08,1:36:06.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,虽然你们这些主人反对我们有安生之所\N{\rENG}Though a host shall encamp against us,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.58,1:36:08.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是我们的心将不会感到恐惧\N{\rENG}our hearts will not fear!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.51,1:36:09.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,准备\N{\rENG}Ready!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.61,1:36:10.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,虽然战争会影响我们\N{\rENG}Though war shall rise against us,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.75,1:36:12.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,但在这方面我们有信心\N{\rENG}in this we will be confident!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.38,1:36:14.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,瞄准\N{\rENG}Aim!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.09,1:36:18.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,叛乱者\N{\rENG}Rebel!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.47,1:37:45.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,来吧\N{\rENG}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.29,1:38:01.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,趴下\N{\rENG}Get down!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.36,1:38:38.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}Will!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.81,1:38:59.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,回来\N{\rENG}Get back!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.83,1:39:13.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我没事\N{\rENG}I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.68,1:41:45.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,切瑞\N{\rENG}Cherry.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.69,1:41:52.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,是纳特，亲爱的\N{\rENG}It's nat, love.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.99,1:41:56.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要停\N{\rENG}Keep on workin'.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.00,1:42:04.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们在找你\N{\rENG}They lookin' for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.94,1:42:09.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们伤了你？\N{\rENG}They hurt you?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.71,1:42:12.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,么有\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.11,1:42:16.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,乔安娜怎么样？\N{\rENG}How's Joanna?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.58,1:42:19.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,她很好\N{\rENG}She fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.88,1:42:22.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,母亲？\N{\rENG}Momma?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.55,1:42:24.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,她也很好\N{\rENG}She fine, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.69,1:42:29.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,手上不要停\N{\rENG}Keep on workin' now.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.59,1:42:32.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,其他人怎么样了？\N{\rENG}Any word on the other men?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.70,1:42:34.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们被吊死了\N{\rENG}They been hanged.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.36,1:42:36.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,所有人\N{\rENG}All of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.90,1:42:41.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们在到处杀人\N{\rENG}They killin' people everywhere
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.74,1:42:44.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,没有理由就因为你是黑人\N{\rENG}for no reason at all but being black.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.58,1:42:51.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们说了会一直杀下去\N{\rENG}They say the killin' won't stop
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.38,1:42:53.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,直到抓到你\N{\rENG}'till they get you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.39,1:43:03.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,这几个月来\N{\rENG}All these months
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.76,1:43:07.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想过\N{\rENG}I thought...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.77,1:43:15.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是不是也死了\N{\rENG}I thought you were dead, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.07,1:43:20.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就在这，亲爱的\N{\rENG}I'm here, love.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.41,1:43:23.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一直都在这\N{\rENG}I'll always be.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.18,1:43:32.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我太想你了\N{\rENG}I miss you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.63,1:43:40.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,切瑞？\N{\rENG}Cherry?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.10,1:43:43.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,你在和谁说话？\N{\rENG}Who you talkin' to?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.97,1:43:48.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在自言自语\N{\rENG}I's just talkin' to myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.57,1:43:55.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,多希望这些事情会有所不同啊\N{\rENG}Wishin' things was different.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.82,1:44:40.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨\N{\rENG}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.10,1:44:49.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是他\N{\rENG}That's him right there!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.57,1:44:51.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,杀了那个黑鬼\N{\rENG}Kill that nigger!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.91,1:45:00.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道你很愤怒，相信我，我也是的\N{\rENG}I know you're angry. Trust me, I am too.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.11,1:45:04.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,这个孩子犯下了屠杀罪，我们将当众吊死他\N{\rENG}This boy committed mass murder and will hang for all to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.65,1:45:06.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,拉他起来\N{\rENG}Get him up.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.60,1:46:36.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,下地狱去\N{\rENG}Go to hell!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.37,1:46:40.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,禽兽\N{\rENG}Animal!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.90,1:47:07.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,吊死他\N{\rENG}Hang him!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.32,1:47:23.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,还有什么要对\N{\rENG}Is there something you wanna say
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.02,1:47:24.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,这些善良人们说的吗？\N{\rENG}to these good people?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.33,1:47:33.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,我准备好了\N{\rENG}I'm ready.


